{"_id":"00n6bknu004e8l47","name":"Dark Presence","type":"Folder","folder":null,"sorting":"a","sort":100000,"color":"#b10d18","flags":{"broken-tales":{"folderKey":"dark-presence","translations":{"es":{"name":"Presencia oscura"}}}}}
{"_id":"01qaf81gg18faq10","name":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[65,66]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Alfred Leaves, el Fantasma Parlante","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 65, 66. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Fácil 3","impulse":"When I am alive, I want to discover all the secrets I can, in order to report them to the One Who Plots in the Shadow / When I am dead, I walk around like a ghost and feel the need to share the secrets I know","oppositionLevel":3}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 65, 66."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"When I am alive, I want to discover all the secrets I can, in order to report them to the One Who Plots in the Shadow / When I am dead, I walk around like a ghost and feel the need to share the secrets I know","oppositionLevel":3}},"items":[{"_id":"00i7mxx99xxm7i00","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","ownerKey":"alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a usurer of secrets, and will sell them at a high price</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 65, 66","key":"descriptor-principal.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a usurer of secrets, and will sell them at a high price","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541840,"modifiedTime":1784372541840,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00hdo4uccu4odh00","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","ownerKey":"alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>If I die, I become a ghost until I am reborn in flesh and blood</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 65, 66","key":"descriptor1-don1.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"If I die, I become a ghost until I am reborn in flesh and blood","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541840,"modifiedTime":1784372541840,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0122nkfeefkn2210","name":"Gift - The Returning Ghost","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","ownerKey":"alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: El fantasma que regresa"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>When Alfred is killed he becomes a ghost and, after one or more Scenes (at the Storyteller's discretion), he will come back to life. When this happens, his Opposition Level goes up one rank (at first Medium 5 and then Hard 7) and he gains 1 Wound. After being killed the third time, Alfred will revert to his normal profile, forgetting who killed him. In ghost form, Alfred has no memories of when he was alive and wanders like a restless soul in the city cemetery. The Opposition Level remains Easy 3 and the Agenda changes.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 65, 66","key":"don1.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"011snyqffqyns110","name":"Gift - Trader of Secrets","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","ownerKey":"alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Comerciante de secretos"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>When the talking Ghost engages in a conversation with someone, he will compel them to share a secret or sin they have committed. A Hunter can oppose the effect of this Gift with a Defense Check. The Talking Ghost always knows a secret related to one or more of the NPCs linked to the Scenario in which he appears.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 65, 66","key":"don2.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"019dv9q77q9vd910","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","ownerKey":"alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 65]<br>60<br>Don: Viajero de mil lugares. Simbad ha visto todo el<br>mundo y gran parte de lo que esconden los cuentos rotos. En<br>el transcurso de una escena, un Cazador puede invocar su<br>ayuda para obtener información o crear un descriptor adi-<br>cional que represente un área específica del conocimiento de<br>Simbad. Sin embargo, el viejo marinero es un tipo excéntri-<br>co, y para conseguir su ayuda primero hay que entretenerlo.<br>El Narrador es quien evalúa la situación actual y el nivel de<br>aburrimiento de Simbad, de modo que el Cazador puede<br>captar el interés de Simbad con acciones creativas, siempre<br>que sean adecuadas a la escena actual.<br>Don: Sé cómo hacerlo. Una vez por escena, un Cazador<br>puede pedir un consejo útil a Simbad y obtener 1 Éxito adi-<br>cional en su prueba. Al igual que con Viajero de mil luga-<br>res, es necesario hacer que Simbad se interese antes de que<br>ayude.<br>•<br>Alfred Leaves, el<br>Fantasma Locuaz<br>Inspirado en Pepito Grillo de Pinocho<br>Presencia oscura de Storymancer Collective<br>(neutral)<br>Érase una vez un rico y poderoso criminal llamado Alfred<br>Leaves. Su negocio y sus armas eran los secretos y todos en<br>Londres tenían asuntos pendientes con él. O, más bien, Leaves<br>había descubierto algún secreto inconfesable y vergonzoso de<br>todos. Se obsesionó cada vez más con los secretos y su sed de<br>conocimiento fue mucho más allá de los asuntos de los mise­<br>rables mortales. ¿Quién creó el mundo? ¿Qué hay después de<br>la muerte? En una locura frenética, Alfred se quitó la vida<br>golpeándose en la sien con un pesado martillo. Tras regresar<br>como un fantasma, se encontró con El Que Conspira en las<br>Sombras y, finalmente, todo se aclaró. Al cabo de unos días,<br>Leaves despertó, vivo otra vez y dispuesto a reemprender su<br>negocio de secretos por cuenta de un nuevo y oscuro maestro.<br>Descriptor:  soy un usurero de secretos y los vendo a un<br>alto precio. Si muero, me convierto en un fantasma hasta que<br>renazco en carne y hueso.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 66]<br>61<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Fácil 3<br>Objetivo: cuando estoy vivo, quiero descubrir todos los secretos que<br>pueda, para informar de ellos a El Que Conspira en las Sombras.<br>Cuando estoy muerto, deambulo como un fantasma y siento la ne­<br>cesidad de compartir los secretos que conozco.<br>Objetivo especial (Carlo, el Títere Viviente): odio la mentira,<br>porque no hace más que devaluar un secreto. Ese pequeño títere<br>animado es la máxima representación del poder de la mentira y<br>quiero que deje de hablar.<br>Nota: Carlo, el Títere Viviente (inspirado en Pinocho), es uno de<br>los Cazadores que aparecen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.<br>Don: El fantasma que regresa. Cuando Alfred muere, se<br>convierte en un fantasma y, después de una o más escenas (a<br>discreción del Narrador), vuelve a la vida. Cuando esto ocurre, su<br>Nivel de Oposición sube un rango (primero Intermedio 5 y luego<br>Difícil 7) y gana 1 Herida. Cuando le han matado por tercera vez,<br>Alfred vuelve a su perfil normal, olvidando quién le ha matado. En<br>forma de fantasma, Alfred no tiene recuerdos de cuando estaba<br>vivo y vaga como un alma inquieta por el cementerio de la ciudad.<br>Sigue teniendo Nivel de Oposición Fácil 3 y su objetivo cambia.<br>Don: Comerciante de secretos. Cuando el Fantasma Locuaz<br>entabla una conversación con alguien, le obliga a compartir un<br>secreto o un pecado que haya cometido. Un Cazador puede resis-<br>tir el efecto de este don con una prueba de defensa. El Fantasma<br>Locuaz siempre conoce un secreto relacionado con uno o más de<br>los PNJs vinculados al escenario en el que aparece.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a rich and powerful criminal named Alfred Leaves. Secrets were his weapons and his business, and there was no one in London who did not have unfinished business with him. Or, more simply, had some unspeakably shameful secret uncovered by Leaves. He became more and more obsessed with secrets, his thirst for knowledge extending far beyond the affairs of miserable mortals. Who had created the world? What was there after death? In a frenzied madness, Alfred Leaves took his life by striking himself on the temple with a heavy hammer. Returning as a ghost, Leaves encountered the One Who Plots in the Shadow. Finally, everything was clear to him. After a few days, Leaves woke up, alive once more and ready to restart his business of secrets on behalf of a new and dark master.</p><p>SPECIAL AGENDA (Carlo the Living Puppet): I hate lying, because it does nothing but devalue a secret. That little animated puppet is the ultimate representation of the power of lying and I want to stop him from speaking.</p><p>Alfred is a recurring enemy who returns stronger each time: OL 3 → OL 5 → OL 7, gaining wounds with each revival. After the third death, he resets and forgets. His Trader of Secrets gift forces people to reveal secrets (Defense Check to resist). He serves the One Who Plots in the Shadow. In ghost form, he loses his living memories but still compels secret-sharing.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 65, 66","key":"source.alfred-leaves-the-talking-ghost","owner":"Alfred Leaves the Talking Ghost","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0156xlvrrvlx6510","name":"Ambrose the Sorcerer (Old Merlin)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[49,50]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Ambrosio el Hechicero (Viejo Merlín)","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 49, 50. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Difícil 7","impulse":"Pretending to be a wise old man who is always ready to help others with the proper advice / Gaining personal advantage by manipulating others","oppositionLevel":7}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 49, 50."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Pretending to be a wise old man who is always ready to help others with the proper advice / Gaining personal advantage by manipulating others","oppositionLevel":7}},"items":[{"_id":"00ta9ikccki9at00","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","ownerKey":"ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient sorcerer, my body is weak, but my magical power is unmatched</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 49, 50","key":"descriptor-principal.ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer (Old Merlin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am an ancient sorcerer, my body is weak, but my magical power is unmatched","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01s9925775299s10","name":"Gift - Ancient Sorcerer","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","ownerKey":"ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Hechicero antiguo"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Merlin's power is incredible, achieving practically anything he can think of through the use of magic. Those who rely on his advice will be able, once per Session, to activate the magic power that the wizard has infused within them. The magical effects must be decided at the time that Merlin blesses the character by defining an appropriate Descriptor such as: Taking flight like a bird or Having skin as hard as a stone. Whoever carries Merlin's magic can activate its power once, obtaining the Descriptor for the entire Scene. Once the Scene resolves the magic is drained from the player and cannot be activated again.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 49, 50","key":"don1.ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer (Old Merlin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01sj8nu66un8js10","name":"Gift - Wise Advice","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","ownerKey":"ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Sabio consejo"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Merlin will never intervene personally but can appear in a dream or vision to his protégés. Once per Scenario, a Hunter can spend 1 Soma to summon Merlin's help. The sorcerer will appear with helpful information or to bless the character with one of his spells.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 49, 50","key":"don2.ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer (Old Merlin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00hsnwgeegwnsh00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","ownerKey":"ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 49]<br>44<br>Ambrosio el Hechicero,<br>también conocido como el Viejo Merlín<br>Inspirado en el Merlín del mito artúrico (neutral)<br>Profundos misterios siguen rodeando a los portadores de la magia y su<br>lucha secreta y secular por el control del mundo arcano. Algunas leyendas<br>hablan de los dos practicantes de las artes arcanas más destacados: Baba<br>Yaga, la bruja obligada a vivir en el cuerpo de una niña, y Ambrosio,<br>constreñido en el cuerpo de un cansado anciano. Bajo el falso nombre<br>de Merlín, Ambrosio lleva siglos moviendo los hilos del destino de la hu­<br>manidad. Finge estar al servicio de los que más lo necesitan, cuando en<br>realidad sus acciones solo fortalecen su posición. Muchos buscan al viejo<br>ermitaño Merlín para solicitar consejo o ayuda, sin saber que el único<br>apoyo que dispensa es el que se da a sí mismo. Con cada nuevo solicitante,<br>el antiguo hechicero se acerca cada vez más al poder absoluto.<br>Descriptor: soy un antiguo hechicero, mi cuerpo es débil, pero mi poder<br>mágico es inigualable.<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Objetivo: fingir ser un anciano sabio que siempre está dispuesto a ayu­<br>dar a los demás con los consejos adecuados. Obtener ventajas personales<br>manipulando a los demás.<br>Objetivo especial (Baba Yaga):  respeto y a la vez odio a Yaga. Su<br>poder es el único que puede enfrentarse al mío. Aunque las leyes de la<br>magia me impiden matarla directamente, nada me prohíbe conducirla al<br>peligro. Y si ella perece debido a su propia estupidez, tanto mejor.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 50]<br>45<br>Objetivo especial (Morgana del Lago): temo el poder de<br>la mayor hechicera de todos los tiempos. Gracias a un acuer­<br>do con Baba Yaga, hemos sellado los recuerdos de la joven<br>Morgana. Haré lo que sea necesario para evitar que despierte.<br>Nota: Morgana del Lago es una de las Cazadoras que apa-<br>recen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.<br>Objetivo especial (Marina, la Exploradora del Mar):<br>respeto a Marina como bruja experta y quiero su ayuda contra<br>Baba Yaga. Obviamente, una vez que mi gran enemiga sea<br>derrotada, tendré que asegurarme de que Marina no ocupe<br>su lugar.<br>Don: Hechicero antiguo. El poder de Merlín es increíble<br>y puede lograr prácticamente cualquier cosa que se le ocurra<br>mediante el uso de la magia. Aquellos que confíen en sus<br>consejos podrán, una vez por sesión, activar el poder que<br>el mago ha infundido en ellos. Los efectos mágicos deben<br>determinarse en el momento en que Merlín bendice al per-<br>sonaje, definiendo un descriptor apropiado como Levantar<br>el vuelo como un pájaro o Tener la piel dura como una piedra.<br>Quien es portador de la magia de Merlín puede activar el<br>poder una vez, obteniendo el descriptor para toda la escena.<br>Una vez que la escena se resuelve, la magia desaparece del<br>personaje y no puede activarse de nuevo.<br>Don: Sabio consejo. Merlín nunca interviene personal-<br>mente, pero puede aparecer ante sus protegidos en un sueño<br>o visión. Una vez por escenario, un Cazador puede gastar 1<br>Soma para convocar la ayuda de Merlín. El hechicero apare-<br>cerá con información útil o para bendecir al personaje con<br>uno de sus hechizos.<br>Cara de Rana<br>Inspirado en El príncipe rana (neutral)<br>Érase una vez el heredero de una familia noble que nació de­<br>forme. Su rostro era ancho y estaba cubierto de pústulas, tenía<br>los ojos enormes y amarillos, y su piel era de un verde parecido<br>al de las ranas. La madre del joven, destrozada por el dolor,<br>quería mantenerlo oculto al mundo hasta que alcanzara la<br>mayoría de edad. Sin embargo, la prematura muerte de su pa­<br>dre le convirtió en el nuevo cabeza de familia. Encerrado por<br>su madre en un mundo de cuentos y mentiras, el joven vástago<br>estaba convencido de ser víctima de una maldición que solo<br>el beso de alguien verdaderamente enamorado podría rom ­<br>per. Durante años, Cara de Rana intentó encontrar el amor y<br>romper el hechizo, recibiendo a cambio rechazo y desprecio.<br>Al borde de la locura, Cara de Rana decidió que si no podía<br>tener el amor verdadero, tomaría el de otra persona. Desde<br>ese día, Cara de Rana viaja acompañado de su fiel sirviente<br>Heinrich. Los dos espían a la gente y, cuando encuentran a<br>una pareja enamorada, secuestran a uno de los amantes para<br>arrebatarle un beso. Esto perpetúa un círculo vicioso de espe­<br>ranza y decepción que siempre culmina con el asesinato de<br>aquellos que, a ojos de Cara de Rana, no alimentan un amor<br>lo suficientemente puro como para romper la maldición.<br>Descriptor: soy un noble rico y deforme que utiliza sus re­<br>cursos para lograr sus propósitos.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Fácil 3<br>Objetivo: encontrar a alguien verdaderamente enamorado<br>y obligarle a besarme para recuperar una apariencia normal.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Deep mysteries still surround wielders of magic and their secret, centuries-old struggle for control of the arcane world. Some legends tell of the two most outstanding practitioners of arcane arts: Baba Yaga, the witch forced into the body of a child, and Ambrose, constrained into the body of a tired old man. Under the false name of Merlin, Ambrose has been pulling the strings of humanity's destiny for centuries. He pretends to be of service to those who need him most, while in truth his actions only strengthen his position. Many seek the old hermit Merlin for advice or help, unaware that the only support he dispenses is that which supports himself. With each new petitioner, the ancient sorcerer grows ever closer to absolute power.</p><p>SPECIAL AGENDAS:<br>- Baba Yaga: I both respect and hate Yaga. Hers is the only power that can stand against mine. While the laws of magic prevent me from killing her directly, nothing prevents me from maneuvering her into danger.<br>- Morgana of the Lake: I fear the power of the greatest sorceress of all time. Thanks to an agreement with Baba Yaga, we have sealed the memory of young Morgana. I will do whatever it takes to keep her from awakening.<br>- Marina the Sea Explorer: I respect Marina as a skilled witch and I seek her aid against Baba Yaga. Obviously, once my great enemy is defeated, I will have to make sure that Marina does not take her place.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 49, 50","key":"source.ambrose-the-sorcerer-old-merlin","owner":"Ambrose the Sorcerer (Old Merlin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01h1o5t11t5o1h10","name":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"fire-eater-the-puppeteer","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[59,60]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Comefuego el Titiritero","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 59, 60. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Listening intently to the personal stories of those I meet and judging who deserves to join my puppet collection / Treating everyone equally, innocents and murderers alike, because life as a puppet is a blessing","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 59, 60."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Listening intently to the personal stories of those I meet and judging who deserves to join my puppet collection / Treating everyone equally, innocents and murderers alike, because life as a puppet is a blessing","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01sb6mlcclm6bs10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","ownerKey":"fire-eater-the-puppeteer","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled alchemist and puppet master</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 59, 60","key":"descriptor-principal.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a skilled alchemist and puppet master","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01t55fo99of55t10","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","ownerKey":"fire-eater-the-puppeteer","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hidden within my clothes are all kinds of tools and weapons, each useful for disassembling and reassembling bodies, whether of flesh or wood</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 59, 60","key":"descriptor1-don1.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"Hidden within my clothes are all kinds of tools and weapons, each useful for disassembling and reassembling bodies, whether of flesh or wood","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01qti32ff23itq10","name":"Gift - The Puppets' Rite","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","ownerKey":"fire-eater-the-puppeteer","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: El ritual de los títeres"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Fire Eater can animate a Puppet by harnessing the soul of a dying person within it. From that moment on, the Puppet will be linked to its creator until he decides to free it. A Puppet has the following profile:<br>Descriptor: I'm an animated puppet and I do everything my creator says... [plus a feature related to what they were in life]<br>1 Wound<br>Opposition Level: Easy 3<br>Gift - Puppet: At zero Wounds a Puppet will shatter, but if repaired it will immediately recover its Wound and return to action. Acting on the part of the Descriptor related to their past life can awaken the dormant consciousness of the harnessed soul, allowing the Puppet to act independently of its master.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 59, 60","key":"don1.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01r3horeeroh3r10","name":"Gift - Master of Puppets","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","ownerKey":"fire-eater-the-puppeteer","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Señor de los títeres"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Fire Eater is always surrounded by at least 6 Puppets. In his presence, increase each Puppet's Opposition Level by 1. When he would suffer 1 Wound, Fire Eater can sacrifice a Puppet instead.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 59, 60","key":"don2.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01up2sleels2pu10","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","ownerKey":"fire-eater-the-puppeteer","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 59]<br>54<br>Comefuego el Titiritero<br>Inspirado por Pinocho (neutral)<br>Érase una vez un hábil titiritero obsesionado con la idea de<br>crear la marioneta perfecta.<br>—Si mis títeres se parecieran a los humanos de verdad —de­<br>cía—, mis espectáculos de marionetas podrían llegar realmente<br>al corazón de la gente.<br>Tras años de estudio, Comefuego encontró un antiguo libro de<br>alquimia que contenía un sangriento ritual capaz de unir el<br>alma de una persona a un cuerpo artificial. Desde ese día, los<br>títeres de su carruaje nunca volvieron a ser los mismos... Cada<br>uno se convirtió en el receptáculo de un alma perdida, añadida<br>a la sombría colección del titiritero.<br>Descriptor: soy un hábil alquimista y titiritero. Entre mis<br>ropas se esconden todo tipo de herramientas y armas, muy útiles<br>para desmontar y volver a montar cuerpos, ya sean de carne o<br>de madera.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: escuchar atentamente las historias personales de<br>quienes conozco y juzgar quién merece formar parte de mi co­<br>lección de marionetas. Tratar a todos por igual, tanto a inocentes<br>como a asesinos, porque la vida como títere es una bendición.<br>Objetivo especial (Carlo, el Títere Viviente): siempre<br>estoy buscando el títere perfecto. Cuando lo encuentre, lo haré<br>mío, cueste lo que cueste.<br>Nota: Carlo, el Títere Viviente, es uno de los Cazadores que<br>aparecen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 60]<br>55<br>Don: El ritual de los títeres. Comefuego puede animar<br>un títere introduciéndole el alma de un moribundo. A partir<br>de ese momento, el títere está ligado a su creador hasta que<br>este decida liberarlo. Un títere tiene el siguiente perfil:<br>Descriptor: soy un títere animado y hago todo lo que<br>mi creador dice... (ver el don Títere, más abajo).<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Fácil 3<br>Don: Señor de los títeres.  Comefuego siempre está<br>rodeado de al menos 6 títeres. En su presencia, aumenta<br>el Nivel de Oposición de los títeres en 1. Cuando sufre 1<br>Herida, Comefuego puede sacrificar a un títere en lugar de<br>sufrirla.<br>Don: Títere. A cero Heridas el títere se rompe, pero si<br>se repara recupera inmediatamente su Herida y vuelve a la<br>acción. El descriptor de cada títere debe completarse con<br>una característica relacionada con lo que fue en vida. Actuar<br>sobre esa parte del descriptor puede despertar la conciencia<br>dormida del alma enjaulada, permitiendo que el títere actúe<br>independientemente de su señor.<br>El Espadachín<br>Enmascarado<br>Inspirado en El Gato con Botas (oponente)<br>Érase una vez un astuto gato que consiguió que su joven amo<br>amasase una fortuna. No obstante, como suele ocurrir, en lu­<br>gar de agradecerlo, el ahora rico vástago se apresuró a aban­<br>donar a su fiel compañero. Decepcionado, el gato se puso al<br>servicio de otros tres amos, pero una vez alcanzado el éxito y<br>la riqueza, todos se deshicieron de él. Así fue como juró que<br>solo trabajaría para sí mismo. En las aventuras que siguieron,<br>el gato liberó a un antiguo espíritu del que obtuvo un deseo.<br>Al enterarse de este milagro, el desagradecido amo original<br>se presentó, compungido ahora tras desarrollar una rara en­<br>fermedad. Se disculpó, arrepintiéndose de su arrogancia, y<br>pidió al gato que deseara una cura. A cambio, le prometió<br>gratitud eterna. El gato aceptó y pidió el deseo. Sin embargo,<br>tan pronto como se realizó el milagro, el viejo amo del gato lo<br>mató, temeroso de sus increíbles aptitudes.<br>Pero hasta un tonto sabe que los gatos tienen nueve vidas,<br>aunque su amo lo hubiera olvidado. Al día siguiente, el gato<br>regresó de entre los muertos y, enfurecido por la traición, juró<br>vengarse. Se puso una máscara capaz de hacerle parecer hu­<br>mano, lo que le permitió hacerse pasar por un noble duelista,<br>y comenzó a viajar por cortes y salones, vengándose de sus<br>ingratos amos. Después de matarlos uno a uno, el gato desa­<br>rrolló el gusto por la sangre y decidió que, a partir de ese día,<br>su único amo sería el dinero.<br>Descriptor: soy un gato astuto que puede fingir ser humano<br>gracias a una máscara mágica. Me pongo al servicio del mejor<br>postor sin reparos y utilizo mis innumerables vidas para salir<br>airoso de cualquier problema.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a skilled puppeteer obsessed with the idea of creating the perfect puppet. \"If only my puppets looked like real humans,\" he said. \"Then my puppet shows could really reach people's hearts.\" After years of study, Fire Eater found an ancient alchemy book containing a bloody ritual capable of binding a person's soul to an artificial body. From that day on, the puppets in Fire Eater's traveling coach were never the same... Each puppet became the receptacle of a lost soul, added to the puppeteer's grim collection.</p><p>SPECIAL AGENDA (Carlo the Living Puppet): I'm always looking for the perfect puppet. Once I find it, I will make it mine, no matter the cost.</p><p>Fire Eater is accompanied by at least 6 Puppets (OL 3, 1 Wound each, increased to OL 4 in his presence). He can sacrifice them to avoid wounds. Each puppet contains a trapped soul that might be awakened by appealing to their past life. The puppets can be repaired if shattered. Extremely dangerous in numbers.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 59, 60","key":"source.fire-eater-the-puppeteer","owner":"Fire Eater the Puppeteer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01yq29qwwq92qy10","name":"Frog Face","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"frog-face","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[50,51]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Cara de Rana","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 50, 51. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Fácil 3","impulse":"Find someone truly in love and force them to kiss me to regain a normal appearance","oppositionLevel":3}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 50, 51."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Find someone truly in love and force them to kiss me to regain a normal appearance","oppositionLevel":3}},"items":[{"_id":"01op1lb55bl1po10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.frog-face","ownerKey":"frog-face","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a wealthy, deformed noble, using my resources to achieve my purposes</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 50, 51","key":"descriptor-principal.frog-face","owner":"Frog Face","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a wealthy, deformed noble, using my resources to achieve my purposes","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00jlokvaavkolj00","name":"Gift - By Any Means","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.frog-face","ownerKey":"frog-face","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Por cualquier medio"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Frog Face's only desire is to break the 'curse' that afflicts him. When he is trying to obtain something that obviously brings him closer to his goal, his Opposition Level becomes Hard 7.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 50, 51","key":"don1.frog-face","owner":"Frog Face","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00jboz6bb6zobj00","name":"Gift - True Love's Kiss","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.frog-face","ownerKey":"frog-face","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Beso de amor verdadero"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>After years of experimental medicine, Frog Face's saliva has acquired strange attributes. Whoever is kissed or licked by Frog Face will go into a daze for the rest of the Scene, lowering their Opposition Level by 2 (in the case of an NPC) or receiving 2 Penalties at each Check (in the case of a Hunter). A Hunter can make a Defense Check to resist the effects of True Love's Kiss.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 50, 51","key":"don2.frog-face","owner":"Frog Face","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"000yoq4zz4qoy000","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.frog-face","ownerKey":"frog-face","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 50]<br>45<br>Objetivo especial (Morgana del Lago): temo el poder de<br>la mayor hechicera de todos los tiempos. Gracias a un acuer­<br>do con Baba Yaga, hemos sellado los recuerdos de la joven<br>Morgana. Haré lo que sea necesario para evitar que despierte.<br>Nota: Morgana del Lago es una de las Cazadoras que apa-<br>recen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.<br>Objetivo especial (Marina, la Exploradora del Mar):<br>respeto a Marina como bruja experta y quiero su ayuda contra<br>Baba Yaga. Obviamente, una vez que mi gran enemiga sea<br>derrotada, tendré que asegurarme de que Marina no ocupe<br>su lugar.<br>Don: Hechicero antiguo. El poder de Merlín es increíble<br>y puede lograr prácticamente cualquier cosa que se le ocurra<br>mediante el uso de la magia. Aquellos que confíen en sus<br>consejos podrán, una vez por sesión, activar el poder que<br>el mago ha infundido en ellos. Los efectos mágicos deben<br>determinarse en el momento en que Merlín bendice al per-<br>sonaje, definiendo un descriptor apropiado como Levantar<br>el vuelo como un pájaro o Tener la piel dura como una piedra.<br>Quien es portador de la magia de Merlín puede activar el<br>poder una vez, obteniendo el descriptor para toda la escena.<br>Una vez que la escena se resuelve, la magia desaparece del<br>personaje y no puede activarse de nuevo.<br>Don: Sabio consejo. Merlín nunca interviene personal-<br>mente, pero puede aparecer ante sus protegidos en un sueño<br>o visión. Una vez por escenario, un Cazador puede gastar 1<br>Soma para convocar la ayuda de Merlín. El hechicero apare-<br>cerá con información útil o para bendecir al personaje con<br>uno de sus hechizos.<br>Cara de Rana<br>Inspirado en El príncipe rana (neutral)<br>Érase una vez el heredero de una familia noble que nació de­<br>forme. Su rostro era ancho y estaba cubierto de pústulas, tenía<br>los ojos enormes y amarillos, y su piel era de un verde parecido<br>al de las ranas. La madre del joven, destrozada por el dolor,<br>quería mantenerlo oculto al mundo hasta que alcanzara la<br>mayoría de edad. Sin embargo, la prematura muerte de su pa­<br>dre le convirtió en el nuevo cabeza de familia. Encerrado por<br>su madre en un mundo de cuentos y mentiras, el joven vástago<br>estaba convencido de ser víctima de una maldición que solo<br>el beso de alguien verdaderamente enamorado podría rom ­<br>per. Durante años, Cara de Rana intentó encontrar el amor y<br>romper el hechizo, recibiendo a cambio rechazo y desprecio.<br>Al borde de la locura, Cara de Rana decidió que si no podía<br>tener el amor verdadero, tomaría el de otra persona. Desde<br>ese día, Cara de Rana viaja acompañado de su fiel sirviente<br>Heinrich. Los dos espían a la gente y, cuando encuentran a<br>una pareja enamorada, secuestran a uno de los amantes para<br>arrebatarle un beso. Esto perpetúa un círculo vicioso de espe­<br>ranza y decepción que siempre culmina con el asesinato de<br>aquellos que, a ojos de Cara de Rana, no alimentan un amor<br>lo suficientemente puro como para romper la maldición.<br>Descriptor: soy un noble rico y deforme que utiliza sus re­<br>cursos para lograr sus propósitos.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Fácil 3<br>Objetivo: encontrar a alguien verdaderamente enamorado<br>y obligarle a besarme para recuperar una apariencia normal.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 51]<br>46<br>Don: Beso de amor verdadero. Tras años de medici-<br>na experimental, la saliva de Cara de Rana ha adquirido<br>extraños atributos. Quien es besado o lamido por Cara de<br>Rana queda aturdido durante el resto de la escena, bajando<br>su Nivel de Oposición en 2 (si es un PNJ) o sufriendo 2<br>Penalizadores en todas las pruebas (si es un Cazador). Un<br>Cazador puede efectuar una prueba de defensa para resistir<br>los efectos del Beso de amor verdadero.<br>Don: Por cualquier medio.  El único deseo de Cara de<br>Rana es romper la “maldición” que le aqueja. Cuando trata<br>de obtener algo que le acerca claramente a su objetivo, su<br>Nivel de Oposición pasa a ser Difícil 7.<br>Heinrich el Fiel<br>Descriptor: soy el viejo cochero de la familia, el único que<br>conoce la verdad sobre mi amo. Con el tiempo, el dolor por su<br>destino me ha vuelto loco.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: ayudar a mi señor a hacer realidad su disparatado<br>sueño, preservándole de una verdad que no aceptaría.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, the heir of a noble family was born deformed. His face was broad and covered with pustules, his eyes huge and yellow, and his skin a frog-like green. Destroyed by grief, the young man's mother wished to keep him hidden from the world until he came of age. However, his father's untimely death made him the new head of the family. Locked in a world of fairytales and lies by his mother, the young scion was convinced that he was the victim of a curse that only a kiss from someone truly in love could break. For years, Frog Face tried to find love and break the spell, receiving in return only rejection and contempt. On the verge of madness, Frog Face decided that if he couldn't have true love, he would take someone else's. Since that day, Frog Face travels accompanied by his trusty servant Heinrich. The two spy on people and when they find a couple in love, they kidnap one of the two lovers to snatch a kiss. This perpetuates a vicious circle of hope and disappointment that always culminates in the killing of those who, in the eyes of Frog Face, do not nurture a love pure enough to break the curse.</p><p>COMPANION: Heinrich the Trustworthy (see separate NPC)<br>Descriptor: I am the old family coachman, the only one who knows the truth about my master. Over time, the grief for his fate has driven me mad.<br>3 Wounds, OL Medium 5<br>Agenda: To help my lord realize his crazy dream, preserving him from a truth he would not accept.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 50, 51","key":"source.frog-face","owner":"Frog Face","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541841,"modifiedTime":1784372541841,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0100hpssssph0010","name":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[63,64]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Ricitos de Oro y sus osos de guerra","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 63, 64. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Live without anyone telling me what I should or can do / Take care of my beautiful blonde hair, the only part of my body that hasn't been spoiled","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 63, 64."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Live without anyone telling me what I should or can do / Take care of my beautiful blonde hair, the only part of my body that hasn't been spoiled","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01nih7cvvc7hin10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","ownerKey":"goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young mercenary who combines fighting skills with uncontrolled fury</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 63, 64","key":"descriptor-principal.goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a young mercenary who combines fighting skills with uncontrolled fury","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01nsgt1uu1tgsn10","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","ownerKey":"goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>My loyal war bears are my family and no one can lay a finger on me</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 63, 64","key":"descriptor1-don1.goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"My loyal war bears are my family and no one can lay a finger on me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01rolbhcchblor10","name":"Gift - War Bears","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","ownerKey":"goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Osos de guerra"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Goldilocks is always accompanied by her three trusty War Bears. The Bears only obey her and it is not possible to influence their behavior or scare them, not even with magic. When Goldilocks acts, she can expend one of her Bears' actions to obtain a single special effect: 1. Inflict 1 additional Wound with a successful attack. 2. Cancel 1 Wound suffered, which a Bear will take instead. 3. Increase the Opposition Level of an action by 1.</p><p>The Three Bears:<br>Fang - 3 Wounds, Opposition Level Easy 3<br>Black - 1 Wound, Opposition Level Hard 7<br>Claw - 2 Wounds, Opposition Level Medium 5<br>Descriptor: We are Goldilocks' children and fight alongside her with unstoppable fury.<br>Agenda: Defending our mother at any cost.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 63, 64","key":"don1.goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00l8mc2dd2cm8l00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","ownerKey":"goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 63]<br>58<br>Orcus puede utilizar su fuerza para apoyar la acción de otro<br>Cazador, el Cazador al que ayude obtiene 2 Éxitos adiciona-<br>les. Al utilizar este don, tira un dado: con un 5 o un 6, Orcus<br>causa involuntariamente un daño irreparable a un objeto, al<br>entorno o a una persona mientras utiliza el don.<br>Don: Guardián de los Cazadores. Una vez por escena, un<br>Cazador puede invocar la protección de Orcus, que sufrirá 1<br>Herida en su lugar. Cuando uses este don, tira un dado: con<br>un 6, Orcus sufre la Herida, pero inflige 1 Herida al Cazador<br>al aplastarlo accidentalmente con su increíble fuerza.<br>•<br>Ricitos de Oro y sus osos<br>de guerra<br>Inspirada en Ricitos de Oro y los tres osos<br>(oponente)<br>Érase una vez una joven huérfana que, para escapar de las<br>garras de una pandilla de ladrones, se refugió en un bosque.<br>Tras vagar durante días, la joven encontró la guarida de un<br>oso y, presa de la desesperación y el hambre, comió la miel<br>que encontró allí. Agotada y muerta de frío, se durmió impru­<br>dentemente en la madriguera. Cuando el oso volvió a casa se<br>abalanzó sobre ella, pero la joven consiguió defenderse con<br>un viejo cuchillo que encontró clavado en los huesos de un<br>cazador descuidado. La joven se impuso al animal salvaje y<br>le cortó el cuello. Antes de morir, el oso le infligió decenas de<br>profundas heridas que malograron su atractivo para siempre.<br>Desesperada, pero decidida a sobrevivir, Ricitos de Oro escuchó<br>un gemido procedente del fondo de la madriguera. Encontró<br>tres osos recién nacidos, huérfanos de la madre que acababa<br>de matar. Se llevó a los cachorros con ella y, desde ese día, pro­<br>metió que nadie volvería a jugar con su vida. Años más tarde,<br>en los campos de batalla se oía con frecuencia el rumor de que<br>Ricitos de Oro y sus osos de guerra eran venerados y temidos<br>como los más peligrosos de todos los mercenarios.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 64]<br>59<br>Descriptor: soy una joven mercenaria que combina sus ha­<br>bilidades de combate con una furia incontrolada. Mis leales<br>osos de guerra son mi familia y nadie puede ponerme un dedo<br>encima.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: vivir sin que nadie me diga lo que debo o puedo ha­<br>cer. Cuidar mi precioso pelo rubio, la única parte de mi cuerpo<br>que no se ha echado a perder.<br>Don: Osos de guerra. Ricitos de Oro siempre va con sus<br>tres fieles osos guerreros. Solo la obedecen a ella y no es po-<br>sible influir en su comportamiento ni asustarlos, ni siquiera<br>con magia. Cuando Ricitos de Oro actúa, puede usar una<br>de las acciones de sus osos para obtener un efecto espe-<br>cial: 1. Infligir 1 Herida adicional con un ataque acertado.<br>2. Cancelar 1 Herida, que sufrirá un oso. 3. Incrementar el<br>Nivel de Oposición de una acción en 1.<br>Los Tres Osos<br>Descriptor:  somos los hijos de Ricitos de Oro y luchamos<br>junto a ella con una furia imparable.<br>Colmillo: 3 Heridas, Nivel de Oposición: Fácil 3<br>Negro: 1 Herida, Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Garra: 2 Heridas, Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: defender a nuestra madre a cualquier precio.<br>Simbad, el Viajero de<br>Mil Mares<br>Inspirado en Simbad de Las mil y una noches<br>(aliado)<br>Érase una vez un hábil marinero que recorrió todos los mares<br>y conoció todas las tierras. Insatisfecho y aburrido, Simbad<br>recurrió a las leyendas más extrañas y oscuras para encontrar<br>algo que pudiera despertar su interés. Conocer los cuentos rotos<br>fue para él el descubrimiento de un nuevo mundo. A partir de<br>ese momento, Simbad se convirtió en un buscador de tesoros<br>prohibidos, hambriento de conocimientos oscuros y secretos<br>ocultos a los ojos de los simples mortales. Solo era cuestión de<br>tiempo que llamara la atención de la Orden. Simbad se puso<br>voluntariamente al servicio de los Cazadores, ofreciendo su<br>gran experiencia a cambio de la rara oportunidad de volver a<br>sentir la emoción del descubrimiento.<br>Descriptor: soy un viajero experimentado y he visto todas<br>las tierras conocidas. Me aburro fácilmente si no me interesa<br>lo que estoy haciendo.<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: estoy dispuesto a hacer cualquier cosa para volver<br>a experimentar la emoción del descubrimiento.<br>Objetivo especial (Sherezade, la Tejedora de<br>Cuentos): me enorgullece conocer todas las historias y leyen­<br>das, y me encanta burlarme de los que se vanaglorian de sus<br>limitados conocimientos. Quiero ridiculizar las historias que<br>cuenta Sherezade, destacando las verdades que solo yo conozco.<br>Nota: Sherezade, la Tejedora de Cuentos, es una de las<br>Cazadoras que aparecen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a young orphan who, to escape the clutches of a gang of thieves, took refuge in a forest. After wandering for days, the young woman found a bear's den and, seized by desperation and hunger, ate the honey she found there. Exhausted and cold, she recklessly fell asleep in the den. When the bear came home it pounced on her, but the girl managed to defend herself with an old knife found stuck in the bones of a careless hunter. The young woman got the better of the feral animal and slit its throat. Before dying the bear inflicted dozens of deep wounds that spoiled her good looks forever. Desperate but determined to survive, Goldilocks heard a moan coming from the bottom of the den. She found three newborn bears, orphans of the mother she just killed. She took the cubs with her and, from that day, promised that no one would ever toy with her life again. Years later, a rumor was heard often across the battlefields, of Goldilocks and her war bears who were revered and feared as the most dangerous of all mercenaries.</p><p>Goldilocks is a mercenary with three War Bears that significantly enhance her combat abilities. The bears can absorb wounds for her, grant +1 Wound on attacks, or boost her OL. The three bears have different profiles:<br>- Fang: 3W, OL 3 (tank)<br>- Black: 1W, OL 7 (elite striker)<br>- Claw: 2W, OL 5 (balanced)<br>They cannot be scared or influenced, even with magic. Total combat package: Goldilocks (3W, OL 5) + 3 Bears (6W total). Extremely dangerous mercenary unit.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 63, 64","key":"source.goldilocks-and-her-war-bears","owner":"Goldilocks and her War Bears","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01k12ztyytz21k10","name":"Hua Mulan the Sword Demon","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[52]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Hua Mulan, el Demonio de la Espada","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 52. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Difícil 7","impulse":"Punishing injustice and righting wrongs using the only tongue the vile can understand – the language of the blade / Deep in my heart I hope to find someone who can show me what true justice is","oppositionLevel":7}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 52."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Punishing injustice and righting wrongs using the only tongue the vile can understand – the language of the blade / Deep in my heart I hope to find someone who can show me what true justice is","oppositionLevel":7}},"items":[{"_id":"01v9eki33ike9v10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","ownerKey":"hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled warrior and have won a thousand battles</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 52","key":"descriptor-principal.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","owner":"Hua Mulan the Sword Demon","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a skilled warrior and have won a thousand battles","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01vje672276ejv10","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","ownerKey":"hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I hate injustice and I know that the way of the sword is the only answer</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 52","key":"descriptor1-don1.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","owner":"Hua Mulan the Sword Demon","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I hate injustice and I know that the way of the sword is the only answer","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01teku5ww5uket10","name":"Gift - Legendary Warrior","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","ownerKey":"hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Guerrera legendaria"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Sword Demon's prowess is unmatched. During the course of a Scene, an enemy will not be able to use the same Gift twice against the Sword Demon. Having seen them in action once, the Demon will always find a way to anticipate the enemy and counter their strategy.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 52","key":"don1.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","owner":"Hua Mulan the Sword Demon","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01u8jn8tt8nj8u10","name":"Gift - The Demon Blade","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","ownerKey":"hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: La hoja del demonio"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Any edged weapon wielded by the Sword Demon becomes lethal. With her weapon, the Demon can cut through solid objects, stop arrows, and even dispel magic. Thanks to her iron will, the Sword Demon can defend herself against any type of attack, canceling the narrative advantage given by any Descriptors.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 52","key":"don2.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","owner":"Hua Mulan the Sword Demon","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0140m9gxxg9m0410","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","ownerKey":"hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 52]<br>47<br>Érase una vez una joven que vivía en<br>el Lejano Oriente. Cuando reclutaron<br>a su anciano padre para la guerra, la<br>joven se hizo pasar por un muchacho<br>para ocupar su lugar, ya que a las mu­<br>jeres no se les permitía ser soldados<br>en aquella época. Bajo el falso nom­<br>bre de Hua Mulan, la joven guerrera<br>ganó todas las batallas y dio gloria a<br>su ejército, pero cuando se descubrió<br>su verdadera identidad, los envidiosos<br>generales la acusaron de engaño y trai­<br>ción. Marcada y exiliada, la guerrera<br>huyó de su hogar, llegando finalmente<br>a Europa tras un largo y errante viaje.<br>Cansada y amargada por encontrar el<br>mismo tipo de injusticia allá donde iba,<br>Hua Mulan decidió que no huiría más.<br>Se disfrazó con su armadura ancestral,<br>ocultando su rostro tras los rasgos de un<br>demonio enfurecido. Bajo el nombre de<br>Demonio de la Espada, la guerrera vaga<br>ahora por Europa, enfrentándose a todo<br>lo que representa el statu quo, como la<br>propia Orden.<br>Descriptor: soy una hábil guerrera y<br>he ganado mil batallas. Odio la injusti­<br>cia y sé que el camino de la espada es la<br>única respuesta.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Objetivo: castigar la injusticia y corre­<br>gir los errores utilizando lo único que los<br>viles pueden entender: el lenguaje de la<br>espada. En el fondo de mi corazón espe­<br>ro encontrar a alguien que pueda mos­<br>trarme lo que es la verdadera justicia.<br>Don: Guerrera legendaria.  La<br>destreza del Demonio de la Espada es<br>inigualable. En el transcurso de una<br>escena, ningún enemigo podrá utili-<br>zar el mismo don dos veces contra ella.<br>Tras haberlo visto en acción una vez, el<br>Demonio siempre encuentra la manera<br>de anticiparse al enemigo y contrarres-<br>tar su estrategia.<br>Don: La hoja del demonio.<br>Cualquier arma de filo blandida por el<br>Demonio de la Espada se vuelve letal.<br>Con su arma, puede cortar objetos sóli-<br>dos, detener flechas e incluso disipar la<br>magia. Gracias a su férrea voluntad, es<br>capaz de defenderse de cualquier tipo<br>de ataque, anulando la ventaja narra -<br>tiva que le otorgan los descriptores<br>asociados.<br>Hua Mulan, el<br>Demonio de la Espada<br>Inspirado en la leyenda de Hua<br>Mulan (oponente)</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a young girl who lived in the Far East. When they drafted her old father for war, the young woman pretended to be a boy to take his place, as women were not allowed to be soldiers at the time. Under the false name of Hua Mulan, the young warrior won every battle and brought glory to her army, but when her true identity was discovered, envious generals took advantage of it to accuse her of deception and betrayal. Branded and exiled, the warrior fled her home, eventually reaching Europe after a long and wandering journey. Tired and embittered at finding the same sort of injustice wherever she went, Hua Mulan decided she would run no more. She made a disguise of her ancestral armor, hiding her face behind the features of a snarling demon. Under the name of the Sword Demon, the warrior now wanders around Europe, wielding her blade against everything that represents the status quo, such as the Order itself.</p><p>The Sword Demon is a powerful opponent who can be an enemy or potential ally depending on the Hunters' approach to justice. Her Demon Blade gift makes her incredibly dangerous as she can cancel Descriptor advantages and dispel magic. Treat her with respect and show understanding of true justice to potentially gain her as an ally.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 52","key":"source.hua-mulan-the-sword-demon","owner":"Hua Mulan the Sword Demon","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01q35ryvvyr53q10","name":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[67,68]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Corazón de Roble, la Dama de los Bosques","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 67, 68. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Find companions willing to look beyond my appearance and treat me with kindness / I am attracted to those who are particularly beautiful, as I secretly desire a lover","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 67, 68."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Find companions willing to look beyond my appearance and treat me with kindness / I am attracted to those who are particularly beautiful, as I secretly desire a lover","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"014f75uaau57f410","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","ownerKey":"oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a twisted, lonely being who wanders the forests and rewards companionship and kindness with boons</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 67, 68","key":"descriptor-principal.oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a twisted, lonely being who wanders the forests and rewards companionship and kindness with boons","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"018vansllsnav810","name":"Gift - Rotten Face","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","ownerKey":"oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Rostro podrido"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Oakheart removes her mask, revealing her terrifying face. Any creature who glimpses it is driven temporarily mad. The madness can take the form of single-minded terror or gibbering catatonia. Create a Descriptor to represent the insanity induced by the vision of Oakheart's face, and inflict 1 Wound on anyone who sees it. Alternatively, Oakheart can bestow its hideous face on a Hunter, who will receive the ability to use this Gift once during the Scenario.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 67, 68","key":"don1.oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0181bupoopub1810","name":"Gift - Blossom Boon","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","ownerKey":"oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Dádiva de flores"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>After experiencing love or true friendship with a person, Oakheart's withered branches burst into bloom, raining petals on her and her new bond. This generates 3 Petal Tokens. Each can be used to heal 1 Wound. Alternatively, you can use 1 Petal to calm a subject in the grip of negative feelings, so that they can ignore Descriptors and Agendas related to the altered state for the rest of the Scene.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 67, 68","key":"don2.oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"003ygfdkkdfgy300","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","ownerKey":"oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 67]<br>62<br>Corazón de<br>Roble, la Dama de<br>los Bosques<br>Inspirado en Blodeuwedd<br>(aliada)<br>Presencia oscura de Chris<br>van der Linden y Chris<br>“Mono” Mahon<br>Los que se aventuran en los bosques oscuros<br>y solitarios hablan en susurros de una mu­<br>jer retorcida, con la piel hecha de corteza,<br>las piernas de raíces enroscadas y el rostro<br>oculto por una tosca máscara de madera.<br>Ofrecida como novia mortal a un dios del<br>bosque hace siglos, la mujer se transformó<br>en un ser horrible para complacer a su nue­<br>vo novio, pero pronto vio cómo su marido<br>se marchitaba y moría al ser talado el bos­<br>que. Ahora, desprovista de su hogar y de su<br>amor, vaga por otros bosques en busca de<br>compañía. Apodada “Corazón de Roble”,<br>se rumorea que cualquier mortal que vis­<br>lumbra su verdadero rostro enloquece al<br>instante por su aterradora apariencia, pero<br>algunos vagabundos afirman haber recibi­<br>do ayuda o incluso ser rescatados por la<br>criatura, que parece sentirse atraída por los<br>viajeros jóvenes y hermosos.<br>Descriptor:  soy un ser retorcido y<br>solitario que vaga por los bosques y<br>recompensa con dádivas la compañía y la<br>amabilidad.<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: encontrar compañeros dispues­<br>tos a mirar más allá de mi apariencia y<br>tratarme con amabilidad. Me atraen los<br>que son especialmente bellos, ya que deseo<br>secretamente un amante.<br>Don: Cara putrefacta.  Si Corazón de<br>Roble se quita la máscara, revelando su<br>aterrador rostro, cualquier criatura que<br>la vea enloquece temporalmente. La lo-<br>cura puede adoptar la forma de un terror<br>absoluto o de una catatonia balbucean-<br>te. Crea un descriptor que represente la<br>locura inducida por la visión del rostro<br>de Corazón de Roble e inflige 1 Herida a<br>cualquiera que lo vea. Alternativamente,<br>puede otorgar su horrible rostro a un<br>Cazador, que recibirá la aptitud de usar<br>este don una vez durante el escenario.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 68]<br>63<br>Don: Dádiva de flores. Tras experimentar el amor o la<br>verdadera amistad con una persona, las ramas marchitas de<br>Corazón de Roble florecen, haciendo llover pétalos sobre ella<br>y su nuevo vínculo. Esto genera 3 Contadores de pétalos,<br>cada uno de los cuales puede usarse para curar 1 Herida.<br>Alternativamente, se puede usar 1 pétalo para calmar a al-<br>guien que esté afectado por sentimientos negativos, de modo<br>que pueda ignorar los descriptores y los objetivos relacio-<br>nados con el estado alterado durante el resto de la escena.<br>Los Feroces Músicos<br>de Bremen<br>Inspirados en Los músicos de Bremen<br>(neutral)<br>Presencia oscura de Claudio Serena<br>Cerca de Bremen, en lo más profundo del norte de Alemania,<br>hay una pequeña posada que los viajeros más experimenta­<br>dos recomiendan evitar, llamada Los Músicos. La posada fue<br>el hogar de muchos refugiados y esclavos maltratados por sus<br>amos o que huían de su pasado, ya que era un lugar seguro<br>donde el largo brazo de la ley no podía encontrarlos. Con el<br>tiempo, también ha atraído a bandidos y criminales de la<br>peor calaña, convirtiéndose finalmente en un lugar embruja­<br>do que los viajeros evitan y las madres utilizan para asustar<br>a los niños que no quieren dormir. Desde el vestíbulo princi­<br>pal se oye una cacofonía de ruidos horribles que ningún ser<br>humano podría emitir. Debido a la violencia que ha tenido<br>lugar allí, la posada ha adquirido vida propia, haciendo suyo<br>el dolor y el miedo de todos los que han buscado refugio en<br>ella. Quien se quede, por error o desesperación, se encontrará<br>con uno de los cuatro aspectos que la posada es capaz de ma­nifestar, es decir, los Músicos: la Bruja, siempre seguida por<br>su gato negro; el Cazador, armado con un cuchillo y acompa­ñado por su sabueso; el Juez, cuya pluma de gallo escribe las<br>faltas de quienes se encuentran con su mirada; y el Monstruo,<br>una criatura informe cuyo rebuzno puede llevar a la locura.<br>Descriptor: soy un lugar lleno de violencia y sufrimiento,<br>capaz de despertar los miedos más profundos en las almas de<br>quienes se acercan.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Those who venture into darkened woods and lonely forests whisper of a twisted woman with skin made of bark, legs made of coiling roots, and a face hidden by a crude wooden mask. Offered as the mortal bride to a forest god centuries ago, the woman was transformed into a hideous being to please her new groom but soon watched her husband wither and die as the forest was cut down. Now bereft of her home and her love, she wanders the woods in search of companionship. Dubbed \"Oakheart,\" it's rumored that any mortal who glimpses her true face is instantly driven mad by her terrifying countenance, but some wanderers claim to have been aided or even rescued by the creature, who seems attracted to young and beautiful travelers.</p><p>Dark Presence by Chris van der Linden and Chris \"Mono\" Mahon.</p><p>Oakheart is a tragic ally seeking companionship. Her Rotten Face can drive enemies mad (1 Wound + insanity Descriptor), or she can gift this ability to a Hunter. If shown love/friendship, she blooms and grants 3 Petal Tokens that heal wounds or calm negative emotions. She's attracted to beautiful travelers. Approach with kindness to gain a powerful forest ally.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 67, 68","key":"source.oakheart-the-lady-of-the-woods","owner":"Oakheart the Lady of the Woods","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01r5x5jccj5x5r10","name":"Orcus the Guardian","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"orcus-the-guardian","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[62,63]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Orcus el Guardián","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 62, 63. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Do my best to serve the Hunters, but avoid killing anyone with my strength","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 62, 63."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Do my best to serve the Hunters, but avoid killing anyone with my strength","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00nmwvvrrvvwmn00","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.orcus-the-guardian","ownerKey":"orcus-the-guardian","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a giant of incredible strength and repulsive appearance</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 62, 63","key":"descriptor-principal.orcus-the-guardian","owner":"Orcus the Guardian","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a giant of incredible strength and repulsive appearance","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00nwwhkqqkhwwn00","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.orcus-the-guardian","ownerKey":"orcus-the-guardian","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I serve the Order as the Hunters' Guardian and execute every order to the best of my ability</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 62, 63","key":"descriptor1-don1.orcus-the-guardian","owner":"Orcus the Guardian","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I serve the Order as the Hunters' Guardian and execute every order to the best of my ability","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"013bd7cooc7db310","name":"Gift - Strength of the Ogre","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.orcus-the-guardian","ownerKey":"orcus-the-guardian","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Fuerza del ogro"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, a Hunter can invoke Orcus's help and use one of the following effects: 1. Orcus can lift, move, or break either an object or part of the environment, with a force equal to that of five men. 2. If Orcus can use his strength to support another Hunter's action, the Hunter he aids will receive 2 Additional Successes. When this Gift is used, roll a die: with a 5 or 6, Orcus unintentionally causes irreparable damage to an object, the environment, or a person while using the Gift.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 62, 63","key":"don1.orcus-the-guardian","owner":"Orcus the Guardian","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0145c0fllf0c5410","name":"Gift - Guardian of the Hunters","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.orcus-the-guardian","ownerKey":"orcus-the-guardian","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Guardián de los Cazadores"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, a Hunter can invoke the protection of Orcus, who will take 1 Wound in his place. When you use this Gift, roll a die: on a 6, Orcus takes the Wound but inflicts 1 Wound on the Hunter by accidentally overwhelming them with his incredible strength.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 62, 63","key":"don2.orcus-the-guardian","owner":"Orcus the Guardian","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00e8ft8dd8tf8e00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.orcus-the-guardian","ownerKey":"orcus-the-guardian","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 62]<br>57<br>Orcus el Guardián<br>Inspirado por El orco maligno (aliado)<br>Érase una vez un hombre gigantesco y deforme con el que<br>nadie quería trabar amistad. Orcus fue objeto de burlas y<br>excluido de la sociedad, hasta que un día conoció a un gentil<br>noble que supo mirar más allá de su repugnante aspecto. El<br>noble convirtió a Orcus en su guardaespaldas personal. Un<br>día, durante un viaje a la capital cercana, el carruaje del no­<br>ble fue atacado por asesinos. Orcus defendió al noble y a su<br>familia con todas sus fuerzas. Perdido en el fragor de la bata­<br>lla, se apoderó del propio carruaje para utilizarlo como arma<br>para aplastar a sus enemigos y, sin saberlo, mató también a<br>todos los pasajeros. Orcus quedó destrozado por el dolor, pero<br>el juez que supervisó el juicio posterior se apiadó de<br>él. Cumpliría su condena como guardián<br>del juez. Sin embargo, la tragedia<br>se repitió. Durante una ca­<br>cería, el incauto juez<br>resbaló por<br>un acantilado y fue salvado por la providencial intervención<br>de Orcus que, con su inmensa fuerza, lanzó al hombre y a su<br>caballo de vuelta al camino. El impacto, no obstante, fue fatal,<br>y el juez acabó destrozado como una manzana madura. Así,<br>de trabajo en trabajo, Orcus siempre era acogido por alguien<br>atraído por sus aptitudes, que finalmente acababa muriendo<br>de forma absurda. Empujó a un rico comerciante para evi­<br>tar que lo atropellara un carro, pero acabó destrozado en la<br>maquinaria de una fábrica cercana... Un médico experto que<br>cayó a un río fue rescatado por Orcus, pero cuando el desven­<br>turado gigante intentó aplicar la técnica de reanimación que<br>le había enseñado su señor, la caja torácica del pobre hombre<br>se resquebrajó y acabó estallando en pedazos por la presión.<br>Después de pasar de señor en señor, Orcus acabó encontrando<br>un hogar en la Orden, quizá el único lugar en el que su her­<br>cúlea fuerza podía aprovecharse con seguridad.<br>Descriptor:  soy un gigante de fuerza increíble y aspecto<br>repulsivo. Sirvo a la Orden como guardián de los Cazadores<br>y cumplo todas las órdenes lo mejor que puedo.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: hacer todo lo posible para ser­<br>vir a los Cazadores, pero evitando matar<br>a alguien con mi fuerza.<br>Don: Fuerza de ogro.  Una vez<br>por escena, un Cazador puede in-<br>vocar la ayuda de Orcus y utilizar<br>uno de los siguientes efectos: 1.<br>Orcus puede levantar, mover o<br>romper un objeto o parte del<br>entorno con una fuerza igual<br>a la de cinco hombres. 2. Si</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 63]<br>58<br>Orcus puede utilizar su fuerza para apoyar la acción de otro<br>Cazador, el Cazador al que ayude obtiene 2 Éxitos adiciona-<br>les. Al utilizar este don, tira un dado: con un 5 o un 6, Orcus<br>causa involuntariamente un daño irreparable a un objeto, al<br>entorno o a una persona mientras utiliza el don.<br>Don: Guardián de los Cazadores. Una vez por escena, un<br>Cazador puede invocar la protección de Orcus, que sufrirá 1<br>Herida en su lugar. Cuando uses este don, tira un dado: con<br>un 6, Orcus sufre la Herida, pero inflige 1 Herida al Cazador<br>al aplastarlo accidentalmente con su increíble fuerza.<br>•<br>Ricitos de Oro y sus osos<br>de guerra<br>Inspirada en Ricitos de Oro y los tres osos<br>(oponente)<br>Érase una vez una joven huérfana que, para escapar de las<br>garras de una pandilla de ladrones, se refugió en un bosque.<br>Tras vagar durante días, la joven encontró la guarida de un<br>oso y, presa de la desesperación y el hambre, comió la miel<br>que encontró allí. Agotada y muerta de frío, se durmió impru­<br>dentemente en la madriguera. Cuando el oso volvió a casa se<br>abalanzó sobre ella, pero la joven consiguió defenderse con<br>un viejo cuchillo que encontró clavado en los huesos de un<br>cazador descuidado. La joven se impuso al animal salvaje y<br>le cortó el cuello. Antes de morir, el oso le infligió decenas de<br>profundas heridas que malograron su atractivo para siempre.<br>Desesperada, pero decidida a sobrevivir, Ricitos de Oro escuchó<br>un gemido procedente del fondo de la madriguera. Encontró<br>tres osos recién nacidos, huérfanos de la madre que acababa<br>de matar. Se llevó a los cachorros con ella y, desde ese día, pro­<br>metió que nadie volvería a jugar con su vida. Años más tarde,<br>en los campos de batalla se oía con frecuencia el rumor de que<br>Ricitos de Oro y sus osos de guerra eran venerados y temidos<br>como los más peligrosos de todos los mercenarios.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a gigantic and deformed man no one wanted to befriend. Orcus was mocked and excluded from society, until one day he met a gentle nobleman who knew how to look beyond his repugnant aspect. The nobleman made Orcus his personal bodyguard. One day, during a trip to the nearby capital, the nobleman's carriage was attacked by assassins. Orcus defended the nobleman and his family with all his might. Lost in the heat of battle, he seized the carriage itself to use as a weapon. He used it to crush his enemies and, unwittingly, killed all the passengers too. Orcus was destroyed by grief, and the Judge who oversaw the trial that followed showed him mercy. He would serve his sentence as a guard for the Judge. But the tragedy only repeated itself. During a hunt, the unwary Judge slipped off a cliff and was saved by the providential intervention of Orcus who, with his immense strength, threw the man and his horse back onto the road. The impact, however, was fatal. The Judge ended up smashed like a ripe apple. From job to job, Orcus was always welcomed by someone attracted by his abilities, who ultimately ended up dying in some absurd way. After going from master to master, Orcus eventually found a home in the Order, perhaps the only place where his Herculean strength could safely be put to good use.</p><p>Orcus is a tragic ally - incredibly strong but prone to accidentally killing those he tries to help. His gifts can provide +2 Successes or take Wounds for Hunters, but there's always a risk (5-6 on d6) of collateral damage. He genuinely wants to help but his strength is a curse. Treat him with kindness and understanding - he's suffered greatly from his accidents.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 62, 63","key":"source.orcus-the-guardian","owner":"Orcus the Guardian","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"00xl9sk22ks9lx00","name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - The Suffering","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[233]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - La que sufre","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 233. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Collect all four pieces of the Compass Rose / Get home to my own time / Find a cure for my disease / Stop the pain and suffering no matter the cost","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 233."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Collect all four pieces of the Compass Rose / Get home to my own time / Find a cure for my disease / Stop the pain and suffering no matter the cost","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01g7yj7bb7jy7g10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 233","key":"descriptor-principal.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - The Suffering","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01ghy4waaw4yhg10","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I was thrown back in time and the only way home is the Compass Rose</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 233","key":"descriptor1-don1.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - The Suffering","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I was thrown back in time and the only way home is the Compass Rose","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01grxql99lqxrg10","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor2-don2.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","sequence":3,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 3"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 233","key":"descriptor2-don2.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - The Suffering","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01eu0iqggqi0ue10","name":"Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor3-don3.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","sequence":4,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 4"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I cover my disfigurement with a silver mask</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 233","key":"descriptor3-don3.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - The Suffering","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I cover my disfigurement with a silver mask","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541842,"modifiedTime":1784372541842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01xu3e6gg6e3ux10","name":"Gift - The Silver Slippers","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Los zapatos de plata"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>OZena wears a pair of enchanted silver shoes permanently attached to her feet. **Short-Range Teleport:** Once per Exchange, OZena can teleport up to 30 feet to any location she can see. This doesn't count as an action and can be used to avoid attacks or reposition instantly. **Long-Distance Teleport:** Once per Scene, OZena can teleport to any location within 1 mile that she has previously visited. This requires her full action. The Silver Slippers cannot be removed without killing her.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 233","key":"don1.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - The Suffering","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01g38cj11jc83g10","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 233]<br>4<br>228<br>las brasas y que está sobre su corazón. No es posible herir a<br>Dose a menos que alguien encuentre primero una forma de<br>penetrar su armadura o utilice un ataque que pueda superar<br>claramente sus defensas.<br>Final de la escena: después de la pelea, Klaus les dice a<br>los Cazadores que el verdadero líder de estos malhechores<br>es una chica con una capa verde a la que llamaban OZena.<br>Les dijo a sus cómplices que ganaran tiempo, mientras ella<br>se encargaba de la bruja. Klaus no vio la cara de la chica,<br>pero por el olor reconoció su propia enfermedad. Ve a la<br>CUARTA ESCENA: El ataque de OZena.<br>CUARTA ESCENA: El ataque<br>de OZena<br>Esta escena concluye la primera parte del escenario<br>y cambia en función de si los Cazadores deciden<br>dejar a alguien en el pueblo mientras van a resca-<br>tar al pequeño Klaus. Dorothea intenta matar a<br>Margareta en su casa. Si ningún Cazador está<br>presente, la bruja sucumbe a los golpes de<br>la joven asesina. Si alguno o todos los<br>Cazadores están presentes, Dorothea<br>huye en cuanto queda claro que está<br>en desventaja.<br>Lugar:  la casa de Marga-<br>reta. Una gran casa circular<br>construida alrededor de un<br>roble centenario.<br>Momento: es tarde por la mañana y la aldea de Gelb ha re-<br>anudado su actividad. Muchos habitantes siguen esperando<br>con tensión en la plaza del pueblo para descubrir la suerte<br>del pequeño Klaus.<br>Información:<br> ◆ Durante el combate, la capucha de Dorothea se desliza<br>hacia atrás y revela su rostro. Es una joven rubia, con<br>ojos de un azul intenso y un abismo supurante en lugar<br>de la nariz.<br> ◆ Cuando Dorothea escapa y se esfuma, los Cazadores<br>descubren que sus zapatillas son mágicas.<br> ◆ Después de la batalla, si sigue viva, Margareta revela<br>detalles sobre la Rosa de los Vientos. Si murió a manos<br>de Dorothea, los Cazadores podrán obtener parte de la<br>información examinando la casa de la bruja.<br>OZena (Dorothea)<br>NO Intermedio 5 – PNJ principal (3 Heridas)<br>Descriptor: soy una chica que quiere volver a su mundo. La<br>enfermedad que me aqueja ha arruinado mi cara y con ella<br>todas las esperanzas de una vida normal. Estoy dispuesta a<br>hacer cualquier cosa para curarme, y por eso me convertí en<br>una asesina de brujas.<br>Objetivo: matar a todas las brujas que me diga Henkle y<br>recuperar las cuatro piezas de la Rosa de los Vientos.<br>Don: Las zapatillas de plata. Quien lleva este artefacto<br>mágico puede moverse a través de los pliegues del espacio,<br>desapareciendo y reapareciendo en un instante. Dorothea<br>puede moverse libremente hasta una distancia máxima de<br>9 metros sin que nadie pueda impedírselo, pero debe poder<br>ver el punto de llegada. Una vez por escena, puede realizar<br>un viaje más largo y reaparecer en cualquier lugar que haya<br>visto al menos una vez.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>OZena is the MAIN ANTAGONIST of the three-part Ozena campaign. She's a Dark Presence but can be REDEEMED. Already killed Johanne (Part 0), now hunts Margareta (Part One), then Helga (Part Two), finally confronts Henkle (Part Three). Knows: Henkle can send people through time, needs all 4 Compass pieces, witches hold pieces. Doesn't know: Henkle is lying, witches are good, incomplete Rose is dangerous, Henkle will abandon her, all orchestrated by One Who Plots in Shadows. If shown compassion and truth, can become ally. Voice: Muffled by mask, tinged with pain and desperation. Mannerisms: Keeps hand on mask, purposeful movements, haunted eyes. Teleportation makes her elusive—hard to pin down in combat.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 233","key":"source.ozena-dorothea-gray-the-suffering","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - The Suffering","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01yn7yxzzxy7ny10","name":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[222]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"San Jorge el Matadragones - Aliado","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 222. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Eliminate Broken Tales that threaten innocent people / Determine if the Hunters are truly heroes or simply monsters / Protect humanity from supernatural threats / Find redemption for killing my childhood friend","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 222."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Eliminate Broken Tales that threaten innocent people / Determine if the Hunters are truly heroes or simply monsters / Protect humanity from supernatural threats / Find redemption for killing my childhood friend","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01a05m8ww8m50a10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a legendary dragon slayer and holy knight of the Church</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 222","key":"descriptor-principal.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a legendary dragon slayer and holy knight of the Church","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01au4fbttbf4ua10","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I hunt monsters and Dark Presences to protect humanity</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 222","key":"descriptor1-don1.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I hunt monsters and Dark Presences to protect humanity","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01ak4tmuumt4ka10","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor2-don2.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","sequence":3,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 3"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The memory of my Dragon friend haunts me</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 222","key":"descriptor2-don2.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"The memory of my Dragon friend haunts me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01be3mprrpm3eb10","name":"Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor3-don3.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","sequence":4,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 4"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I watch to determine if Hunters are heroes or monsters</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 222","key":"descriptor3-don3.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I watch to determine if Hunters are heroes or monsters","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0109jg9339gj9010","name":"Gift - The Holy Dragon Slayer","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: El santo matadragones"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Saint George wields a blessed sword that once slew his Dragon friend. When fighting against creatures with monstrous, magical, or supernatural Descriptors, Saint George can spend 1 Fervor Token to inflict 1 additional Wound beyond normal damage, or 1 Wound even if the target succeeds on their Defense Check. The only way to avoid this Wound is to have an Outcome with Increment and spend it to nullify the Gift's effect. Saint George regenerates Fervor Tokens equal to the number of Hunters at the beginning of each Scenario when acting as an ally.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 222","key":"don1.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"010jj1y22y1jj010","name":"Gift - The Judgment of the Saint","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: El juicio del santo"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Saint George keeps everyone under observation, even when fighting alongside the Hunters. During a Scene, if a Hunter activates their Dark Ego to perform a good deed, or uses any Gift that allows them to use magic or manipulate ordinary people to do good in Saint George's presence, he adds 1 Judgment Token to this Gift. Judgment Tokens carry over between Scenarios. When Judgment Tokens equal twice the number of Hunters, Saint George makes amends, declaring he was wrong in his judgment, and puts an end to any Witch Hunt, becoming a permanent ally. Examples: Using Dark Ego to save innocent lives, employing magic to heal/protect the helpless, manipulating nobles to bring justice, sacrificing personal gain to help others.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 222","key":"don2.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"014545s22s545410","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 222]<br>217<br>Érase una<br>vez...<br>San Jorge, un valiente y devoto guerrero que<br>hizo de la lucha contra los monstruos su ra-<br>zón de vivir, es quizá el miembro más impor-tante y poderoso de la Orden, pero su celo a la<br>hora de castigar a los cuentos rotos puede ser<br>también una amenaza para los Cazadores...<br>Quizá el verdadero enemigo no se esconde en<br>las sombras, sino que camina a su lado...<br>La historia que ha<br>llevado hasta aquí...<br>San Jorge, el Matadragones es un escenario especial<br>que puede utilizarse durante cualquier campaña o para una<br>partida corta. De hecho, una vez que San Jorge haya sido<br>incluido como apoyo a los Cazadores, dispondrá de varios<br>métodos para frustrar sus planes, ya sea mediante amigos<br>o enemigos. Luchará junto a los Cazadores, pero su mirada<br>severa y su espíritu inquisitorial deben mantenerse a raya<br>para que el santo no desate la furia de la Iglesia contra sus<br>propios agentes.<br>Cómo utilizar a San Jorge<br>San Jorge se unirá al grupo de Cazadores en cuanto hayan<br>resuelto algunos escenarios y obtenido un poco de fama.<br>Como presencia oscura aliada, apoyará a los Cazadores en<br>sus viajes. Sin embargo, pronto quedará claro que su afán<br>por todo lo relacionado con los cuentos rotos hará que sea<br>difícil de manejar.<br>San Jorge dispone de un don llamado El juicio del santo.<br>Cuando se hayan acumulado suficientes Contadores de sos-<br>pecha, el santo se convertirá en una presencia oscura opo-<br>nente y tratará de detener a los Cazadores, ya que los consi-<br>derará representantes de la oscuridad que la Iglesia combate.<br>San Jorge<br>(presencia oscura aliada)<br>Érase una vez un niño alegre llamado Jorge que a menudo<br>se alejaba de casa para correr y jugar en el bosque. Un día se<br>cayó al río y, en un abrir y cerrar de ojos, se estaba ahogando.<br>Al borde de la muerte, el niño sintió que una fuerza increíble<br>le empujaba a la superficie y pronto se encontró en la orilla,<br>calado hasta los huesos, pero vivo. Su salvador era una ex­<br>traña criatura con aspecto de lagarto y ojos increíblemente<br>humanos. ¡Un dragón!, pensó el niño, lanzándose al cuello<br>de la criatura, y entre ambos nació una profunda amistad.<br>En los años siguientes, Jorge aprovechó cualquier oportuni­<br>dad para encontrarse con su amigo secreto y aprender de él<br>las maravillas de la magia y lo que se oculta a los ojos de la<br>gente corriente. Entonces, una plaga asoló el pueblo donde<br>vivía Jorge, matando a sus padres. Las peticiones de ayuda del<br>muchacho cayeron en saco roto, a pesar de que la criatura era<br>capaz de curar cualquier enfermedad. El dragón, por miedo a</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Saint George is a RECURRING campaign element who can transition between ally and opponent based on Hunter actions. Track Fervor Tokens (combat resource) and Judgment Tokens (redemption mechanic) secretly. He can appear in multiple scenarios, building tension over time. If Hunters discover his manipulated past and appeal to his Dragon friend's memory, reduce OL by 1 for that Scene as his resolve wavers. Connection to One Who Plots in the Shadows makes him a bridge to discovering the true enemy. Voice: Noble and commanding, but with underlying sadness. Mannerisms: Touches his sword hilt when troubled, distant gaze.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 222","key":"source.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-ally","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"00wxb9twwt9bxw00","name":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Opponent","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[223,224]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"San Jorge el Matadragones - Oponente","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 223, 224. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Hunt down and eliminate the Hunters who have proven themselves villains / Protect the Church and humanity from corrupted Order agents / Bring justice to those who abuse their power / Prevent more innocents from being harmed by these monsters","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 223, 224."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Hunt down and eliminate the Hunters who have proven themselves villains / Protect the Church and humanity from corrupted Order agents / Bring justice to those who abuse their power / Prevent more innocents from being harmed by these monsters","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00fkyr6pp6rykf00","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the Dragon Slayer, and I have seen the truth</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 223, 224","key":"descriptor-principal.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Opponent","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am the Dragon Slayer, and I have seen the truth","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00eqzy3ss3yzqe00","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>These so-called Hunters are monsters wearing human skin</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 223, 224","key":"descriptor1-don1.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Opponent","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"These so-called Hunters are monsters wearing human skin","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00f0zjsrrsjz0f00","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor2-don2.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","sequence":3,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 3"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>They must be eliminated before they corrupt more innocents</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 223, 224","key":"descriptor2-don2.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Opponent","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"They must be eliminated before they corrupt more innocents","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00gexk9mm9kxeg00","name":"Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor3-don3.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","sequence":4,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 4"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Church and humanity must be protected from corrupted agents</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 223, 224","key":"descriptor3-don3.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Opponent","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"The Church and humanity must be protected from corrupted agents","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0120ux7qq7xu0210","name":"Gift - Witch Hunt","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Caza de brujas"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>When he becomes an Opponent Dark Presence, Saint George acquires Fervor Tokens equal to the number of Hunters. When facing a Hunter he's been tracking down, he can spend 1 Fervor Token to inflict 1 additional Wound on top of normal damage, or just 1 Wound if the Hunter succeeds on their Defense Check. The only way to avoid this Wound is to have an Outcome with Increment and spend it to nullify the Gift's effect. Saint George can also spend 1 Fervor Token to transform any Position Check's result for an action against him into a Failure, so long as the Hunter performing it has at least one Descriptor related to magic or a monstrous characteristic. Saint George regenerates Fervor Tokens equal to the number of Hunters at the beginning of each Scenario.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 223, 224","key":"don1.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Opponent","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00jdv2hffh2vdj00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","ownerKey":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 223]<br>218<br>ser descubierto y que lo mataran, se negó a curar a la gente del pueblo. Pasaron<br>veinte años y Jorge hizo sus votos, convirtiéndose en un luchador sagrado al<br>servicio del Papado y liderando más de una batalla contra las fuerzas del<br>mal. Cuando el santo regresó a su antigua aldea, se adentró en el bosque<br>en busca de su viejo amigo. El dragón se alegró de volver a ver a Jorge<br>después de tanto tiempo y salió... solo para darse cuenta de que había<br>acudido ante su verdugo.<br>NO Intermedio 5 – (4 Heridas)<br>Descriptor: soy un caballero sagrado al servicio de la Iglesia. Estoy<br>capacitado para cazar y derrotar a cualquier monstruo. Nada escapa a<br>mi mirada inquisitiva.<br>Objetivo: encontrar a todas las criaturas vinculadas a los cuentos rotos y<br>exterminarlas para que no puedan causar ningún daño. Comprender verda­<br>deramente la naturaleza de los cuentos rotos.<br>Don: El juicio del santo.  San Jorge tiene a todo el mundo controlado, incluso a<br>los Cazadores a los que acompaña. Durante una escena, si un Cazador activa su ego<br>oscuro o utiliza cualquier don que le permita emplear la magia o aterrorizar a la gente<br>corriente en presencia de San Jorge, añade 1 Contador de sospecha a este don. Durante<br>una escena, San Jorge puede mantener a un Cazador bajo vigilancia, haciéndolo sentir<br>incómodo. Cuando lo hace, el Narrador puede gastar 1 Contador de sospecha para<br>imponer 1 Penalizador a la prueba de un Cazador. Los Contadores de sospecha<br>se mantienen entre los escenarios. Cuando los Contadores de sospecha son<br>iguales al doble del número de Cazadores, San Jorge emprende una Caza de<br>brujas y se convierte en una presencia oscura oponente.<br>Don: El santo cazador de dragones. San Jorge comienza el escena-<br>rio con 1 Contador de fervor. Cuando se enfrenta a un enemigo que es<br>visiblemente monstruoso, puede gastar 1 Contador de fervor para<br>permitir que un Cazador aliado le inflija 1 Herida adicional.<br>Cuando dicho enemigo revela uno de sus dones, San<br>Jorge puede gastar 1 Contador de fervor para conce-<br>der 2 Éxitos adicionales en una prueba de defensa a<br>cualquier Cazador aliado. Al sufrir 1 Herida, San<br>Jorge obtiene 1 Contador de fervor.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 224]<br>219<br>Cómo gestionar a San Jorge<br>Una vez introducido en una Campaña o escenario, San Jorge<br>es una presencia recurrente a la que los Cazadores deben<br>rendir cuentas. Como máximo representante del Papado, el<br>santo tiene plena autoridad sobre los miembros de la Orden.<br>Los Cazadores pronto sabrán que San Jorge puede ser un<br>buen aliado, pero que bajo su severa mirada no todo está<br>permitido.<br> ◆ El Narrador puede añadir a San Jorge al grupo a lo<br>largo de un escenario. Aunque tenga autoridad para<br>tomar todas las decisiones, no sería divertido jugar la<br>sesión con un PNJ que guíe a los Cazadores por una<br>correa. Por lo tanto, el santo permanecerá en un segun-<br>do plano, con curiosidad por observar a los Cazadores<br>y su trabajo como miembros de la Orden. El Narrador<br>debe dejar claro inmediatamente que el santo está a su<br>disposición con sus dones, pero que El juicio del santo<br>puede convertirle rápidamente en un enemigo.<br> ◆ El Narrador puede añadir a San Jorge al grupo, pero<br>el santo actuará de forma independiente y aparecerá<br>solo en algunas escenas. De este modo, el santo ejercerá<br>más presión sobre los Cazadores, juzgando comporta-<br>mientos que considera impropios de un miembro de la<br>Orden. Siempre dará apoyo con sus dones, pero el<br>Narrador podrá utilizarlo más como una molestia que<br>otra cosa.<br> ◆ El Narrador solo dejará intervenir a San Jorge cuando<br>esté claro que una criatura monstruosa aparecerá en<br>el escenario. Por ejemplo, en Iskra de la caperucita roja<br>podría llegar tras la aparición de Greskar (página 125)<br>o debido la presencia del Antiguo Enemigo como pre-<br>sencia oscura (página 49). San Jorge acudirá impulsado<br>por la premonición de que hay un monstruo que cazar<br>y abatir. El santo se mostrará abierto y solidario con los<br>Cazadores, al menos hasta que haya acumulado el pri-<br>mer Contador de sospecha. Esta es una buena manera<br>de introducir a San Jorge en una campaña por primera<br>vez.<br> ◆ Una vez que los Contadores de sospecha acumulados<br>sean el doble del número de Cazadores, San Jorge ini-<br>ciará una Caza de brujas y se convertirá en una pre-<br>sencia oscura oponente con el perfil correspondiente.<br>A partir de ese momento, como cualquier oponente, el<br>Narrador podrá utilizarlo para obstaculizar a los<br>Cazadores y crear un escenario especial que lleve al en-<br>frentamiento final con San Jorge.<br>San Jorge<br>(presencia oscura oponente)<br>El luchador sagrado que erradica la oscuridad en todas sus<br>formas. Tiene hábiles paladines a su servicio, dispuestos a<br>cumplir todas sus órdenes.<br>NO Intermedio 5 – (4 Heridas)<br>Descriptor: soy un caballero devoto al servicio de la Iglesia.<br>Soy experto en cazar y capturar cualquier manifestación de<br>la oscuridad. Conozco a todos los Cazadores de la Orden y sé<br>cómo derrotarlos.<br>Objetivo: encontrar a los Cazadores que han demostrado<br>estar vinculados a los cuentos rotos y encerrarlos en las cár ­<br>celes de la Iglesia. Quien se oponga a mi sentencia perecerá,<br>sufriendo el juicio de Dios.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Saint George as OPPONENT is a persistent antagonist who appears throughout the campaign. The transition should be dramatic: public confrontation, evidence revealed, one chance to surrender, then summons Paladins (number = Hunters). During Witch Hunt: appears at worst moments, turns allies against Hunters, disrupts plans. Can still be redeemed by accumulating Judgment Tokens (twice number of Hunters) through good deeds. Brings unique Paladins equal to Hunter number (roll 1d6 to determine which). Voice: Harsh and accusatory, filled with righteous fury. Mannerisms: Points accusingly, quotes scripture, unwavering conviction.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 223, 224","key":"source.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-opponent","owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Opponent","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"00r0vdjoojdv0r00","name":"Sherazade - The Weaver of Tales","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[205,206]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Sherezade - La Tejedora de Cuentos","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 205, 206. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Punish all those who believe they can change the world for the better / Find peace and smile once again","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 205, 206."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Punish all those who believe they can change the world for the better / Find peace and smile once again","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00r6i5ylly5i6r00","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","ownerKey":"sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a storyteller who can bring the characters I invent to life</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 205, 206","key":"descriptor-principal.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","owner":"Sherazade - The Weaver of Tales","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a storyteller who can bring the characters I invent to life","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00qcjcvoovcjcq00","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","ownerKey":"sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>My charm is so beguiling that it cannot be ignored</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 205, 206","key":"descriptor1-don1.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","owner":"Sherazade - The Weaver of Tales","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"My charm is so beguiling that it cannot be ignored","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01j431sqqs134j10","name":"Gift - Words like Honey","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","ownerKey":"sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Palabras como miel"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Sherazade can tell one of her stories to bring out a memory, an emotion, or a fear. Highlight 1 Keyword from this brief story. If a Hunter or NPC hears the story and is linked to the Keyword, the related emotion will awaken, leading them to open up to Sherazade and share something about themselves.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 205, 206","key":"don1.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","owner":"Sherazade - The Weaver of Tales","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01iu3g3rr3g3ui10","name":"Gift - A Thousand and One Nights","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","ownerKey":"sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Las mil y una noches"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>One of the characters from a Scenario already faced by the Hunters comes to life as a Shadow. Create a Descriptor to represent it. The Shadow thus created will be at the service of Sherazade and will do whatever they are ordered. Shadows cannot speak nor act in places where there is more light than shadow. During a Scene, Sherazade can create a number of Shadows equal to the Hunters she is facing plus one. For each Hunter who has been affected by Words like Honey, Sherazade can summon an additional Shadow.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 205, 206","key":"don2.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","owner":"Sherazade - The Weaver of Tales","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00men98vv89nem00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","ownerKey":"sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 205]<br>200<br>Sherezade,<br>la Tejedora de Cuentos<br>(presencia oscura oponente)<br>Sherezade era una joven narradora de cuentos que, junto con su her­<br>mana Dinarzad, fue capturada y llevada a la corte de un rico sultán.<br>El sultán era un hombre de alma oscura que disfrutaba infligiendo<br>miedo y dolor a otras personas, y que inventaba excusas triviales para<br>atormentar a los pobres inocentes. El libertino y rico hombre decidió<br>jugar un juego con Sherezade. Cada noche tenía que contarle una<br>historia. Si le gustaba, la ejecución de Dinarzad se aplazaría un día.<br>Después de treinta días de cuentos, las dos hermanas se ganarían su<br>libertad. Sherezade creaba una nueva historia cada noche, siempre<br>con la amenaza de disgustar al sultán y condenar así a su querida<br>hermana. Pero cada noche, el sultán quedaba maravillado por la<br>belleza de los cuentos de Sherezade y le concedía un día más. Así<br>transcurrieron los fatídicos treinta días y en la mañana del trigési­<br>mo primero, Sherezade fue convocada por el sultán. El hombre se<br>arrojó a sus pies, llorando, tras haber hecho ejecutar a Dinarzad<br>la primera noche, seguro del fracaso de Sherezade y deseoso<br>de verla desesperada incluso si tenía éxito. Pero ahora, tras<br>más de treinta noches de bellas historias, el corazón del sul­<br>tán se llenó de amor y admiración por Sherezade. La quería<br>a su lado como su novia. El sultán ofreció a Sherezade su<br>riqueza, poder y todo lo que pudiera desear para olvidar a<br>Dinarzad y su muerte. Pero Sherezade tenía la sonrisa de su<br>hermana grabada en su mente como el último momento feliz<br>que podía recordar, algo que ni siquiera la gran riqueza del<br>sultán podría borrar. Y así, todas las historias contadas toma­<br>ron forma como sombras negras que emergían de las paredes para<br>apoderarse del sultán y condenarlo a una terrible oscuridad durante</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 206]<br>201<br>toda la eternidad. Vacía de emociones, Sherezade vagó por<br>todo el mundo conocido y finalmente encontró a un hombre<br>cansado y encorvado, un escritor que, como ella, había visto<br>destruidos todos sus recuerdos felices por el egoísmo de otros.<br>Ambos forjaron una amarga alianza para dar nueva vida a las<br>historias, ahora rotas por el deseo del Niño Salvador.<br>NO Intermedio 5 – (3 Heridas)<br>Descriptor: soy una narradora capaz de dar vida a los per­<br>sonajes que invento. Mis encantos son tan seductores que no<br>pueden ignorarse.<br>Objetivo: castigar a todos los que creen que pueden cambiar<br>el mundo a mejor. Encontrar la paz y volver a sonreír.<br>Don: Las mil y una noches. Uno de los personajes de un<br>escenario al que ya se han enfrentado los Cazadores cobra<br>vida como una Sombra. Crea un descriptor para represen-<br>tarla. La Sombra así creada estará al servicio de Sherezade<br>y hará lo que le ordene. Las Sombras no pueden hablar ni<br>actuar en lugares donde haya más luz que sombra. Durante<br>una escena, Sherezade puede crear un número de Sombras<br>igual a los Cazadores a los que se enfrenta más una. Por cada<br>Cazador que haya sido afectado por Palabras me-<br>losas, Sherezade puede convocar una Sombra<br>adicional.<br>Don: Palabras melosas. Sherezade<br>puede contar una de sus historias para<br>hacer aflorar un recuerdo, una emoción<br>o un miedo. Destaca 1 palabra clave<br>de esta breve historia. Si un Cazador<br>o PNJ escucha la historia y está vin-<br>culado a la palabra clave, la emoción<br>relacionada se despertará, haciendo<br>que se abra a Sherezade y comparta<br>algo sobre sí mismo.<br>Las Sombras<br>Las Sombras de Sherezade no son más que el oscuro reflejo<br>de lo que fueron en la historia de la que proceden.<br>Ver página 197.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A young storyteller who, together with her sister Dinarzad, was captured and taken to the court of a wealthy Sultan. The Sultan played a cruel game: every night Sherazade had to tell him a story. If he liked it, Dinarzad's execution would be postponed for a day. After thirty days, they would earn freedom. Sherazade succeeded for over thirty nights, but the Sultan had executed Dinarzad on the first night, certain of failure and eager to see Sherazade's despair. When he revealed this, throwing himself at her feet in love, all her stories took shape as black shadows that seized the Sultan and held him in terrible darkness for eternity. Empty of emotion, she wandered the world and met a tired writer who, like her, had seen every happy memory destroyed by others' selfishness. The two forged a bitter alliance to bring new life into stories now broken by the wish of the Child Savior. She seduces courts with dark stories about Hunters, then brings characters from those stories to life as monstrous shadows to steal mortal souls.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 205, 206","key":"source.sherazade-the-weaver-of-tales","owner":"Sherazade - The Weaver of Tales","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01684oyzzyo48610","name":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[64,65]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Simbad, el viajero de mil mares","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 64, 65. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"I am willing to do anything to experience the thrill of discovery once again","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 64, 65."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am willing to do anything to experience the thrill of discovery once again","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"007o7dummud7o700","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","ownerKey":"sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an experienced traveler and have seen every known land</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 64, 65","key":"descriptor-principal.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am an experienced traveler and have seen every known land","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"007e7s5nn5s7e700","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","ownerKey":"sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I get bored easily if I'm not interested in what I'm doing</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 64, 65","key":"descriptor1-don1.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I get bored easily if I'm not interested in what I'm doing","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00c3crihhirc3c00","name":"Gift - Traveler of a Thousand Places","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","ownerKey":"sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Viajero de mil lugares"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Sinbad has seen the whole world and much of what the Broken Tales hide. In the course of a Scene, a Hunter can invoke his help to obtain information or create an additional Descriptor that represents a specific area of Sinbad's knowledge. But the old sailor is an eccentric type, and to provide his help he first must be entertained. The Storyteller will evaluate the current situation and Sinbad's level of boredom. A Hunter can capture Sinbad's interest with creative actions, as long as they're appropriate to the current Scene.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 64, 65","key":"don1.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00b9dyfkkfyd9b00","name":"Gift - I Know How To Do It","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","ownerKey":"sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Sé cómo hacerlo"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, a Hunter can get 1 Additional Success in his Check, asking Sinbad for helpful advice. As with Traveler of a Thousand Places, Sinbad needs to be intrigued before helping.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 64, 65","key":"don2.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00xshrmccmrhsx00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","ownerKey":"sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 64]<br>59<br>Descriptor: soy una joven mercenaria que combina sus ha­<br>bilidades de combate con una furia incontrolada. Mis leales<br>osos de guerra son mi familia y nadie puede ponerme un dedo<br>encima.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: vivir sin que nadie me diga lo que debo o puedo ha­<br>cer. Cuidar mi precioso pelo rubio, la única parte de mi cuerpo<br>que no se ha echado a perder.<br>Don: Osos de guerra. Ricitos de Oro siempre va con sus<br>tres fieles osos guerreros. Solo la obedecen a ella y no es po-<br>sible influir en su comportamiento ni asustarlos, ni siquiera<br>con magia. Cuando Ricitos de Oro actúa, puede usar una<br>de las acciones de sus osos para obtener un efecto espe-<br>cial: 1. Infligir 1 Herida adicional con un ataque acertado.<br>2. Cancelar 1 Herida, que sufrirá un oso. 3. Incrementar el<br>Nivel de Oposición de una acción en 1.<br>Los Tres Osos<br>Descriptor:  somos los hijos de Ricitos de Oro y luchamos<br>junto a ella con una furia imparable.<br>Colmillo: 3 Heridas, Nivel de Oposición: Fácil 3<br>Negro: 1 Herida, Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Garra: 2 Heridas, Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: defender a nuestra madre a cualquier precio.<br>Simbad, el Viajero de<br>Mil Mares<br>Inspirado en Simbad de Las mil y una noches<br>(aliado)<br>Érase una vez un hábil marinero que recorrió todos los mares<br>y conoció todas las tierras. Insatisfecho y aburrido, Simbad<br>recurrió a las leyendas más extrañas y oscuras para encontrar<br>algo que pudiera despertar su interés. Conocer los cuentos rotos<br>fue para él el descubrimiento de un nuevo mundo. A partir de<br>ese momento, Simbad se convirtió en un buscador de tesoros<br>prohibidos, hambriento de conocimientos oscuros y secretos<br>ocultos a los ojos de los simples mortales. Solo era cuestión de<br>tiempo que llamara la atención de la Orden. Simbad se puso<br>voluntariamente al servicio de los Cazadores, ofreciendo su<br>gran experiencia a cambio de la rara oportunidad de volver a<br>sentir la emoción del descubrimiento.<br>Descriptor: soy un viajero experimentado y he visto todas<br>las tierras conocidas. Me aburro fácilmente si no me interesa<br>lo que estoy haciendo.<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: estoy dispuesto a hacer cualquier cosa para volver<br>a experimentar la emoción del descubrimiento.<br>Objetivo especial (Sherezade, la Tejedora de<br>Cuentos): me enorgullece conocer todas las historias y leyen­<br>das, y me encanta burlarme de los que se vanaglorian de sus<br>limitados conocimientos. Quiero ridiculizar las historias que<br>cuenta Sherezade, destacando las verdades que solo yo conozco.<br>Nota: Sherezade, la Tejedora de Cuentos, es una de las<br>Cazadoras que aparecen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 65]<br>60<br>Don: Viajero de mil lugares. Simbad ha visto todo el<br>mundo y gran parte de lo que esconden los cuentos rotos. En<br>el transcurso de una escena, un Cazador puede invocar su<br>ayuda para obtener información o crear un descriptor adi-<br>cional que represente un área específica del conocimiento de<br>Simbad. Sin embargo, el viejo marinero es un tipo excéntri-<br>co, y para conseguir su ayuda primero hay que entretenerlo.<br>El Narrador es quien evalúa la situación actual y el nivel de<br>aburrimiento de Simbad, de modo que el Cazador puede<br>captar el interés de Simbad con acciones creativas, siempre<br>que sean adecuadas a la escena actual.<br>Don: Sé cómo hacerlo. Una vez por escena, un Cazador<br>puede pedir un consejo útil a Simbad y obtener 1 Éxito adi-<br>cional en su prueba. Al igual que con Viajero de mil luga-<br>res, es necesario hacer que Simbad se interese antes de que<br>ayude.<br>•<br>Alfred Leaves, el<br>Fantasma Locuaz<br>Inspirado en Pepito Grillo de Pinocho<br>Presencia oscura de Storymancer Collective<br>(neutral)<br>Érase una vez un rico y poderoso criminal llamado Alfred<br>Leaves. Su negocio y sus armas eran los secretos y todos en<br>Londres tenían asuntos pendientes con él. O, más bien, Leaves<br>había descubierto algún secreto inconfesable y vergonzoso de<br>todos. Se obsesionó cada vez más con los secretos y su sed de<br>conocimiento fue mucho más allá de los asuntos de los mise­<br>rables mortales. ¿Quién creó el mundo? ¿Qué hay después de<br>la muerte? En una locura frenética, Alfred se quitó la vida<br>golpeándose en la sien con un pesado martillo. Tras regresar<br>como un fantasma, se encontró con El Que Conspira en las<br>Sombras y, finalmente, todo se aclaró. Al cabo de unos días,<br>Leaves despertó, vivo otra vez y dispuesto a reemprender su<br>negocio de secretos por cuenta de un nuevo y oscuro maestro.<br>Descriptor:  soy un usurero de secretos y los vendo a un<br>alto precio. Si muero, me convierto en un fantasma hasta que<br>renazco en carne y hueso.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a skilled sailor who traveled every sea and witnessed every land. Dissatisfied and bored, Sinbad turned to the strangest and darkest legends to find something that could arouse his interest. Learning of The Broken Tales was for him the discovery of a new world. From that moment on, Sinbad became a seeker of forbidden treasures, hungry for dark knowledge and secrets concealed from the eyes of mere mortals. It was only a matter of time before he caught the attention of the Order. Sinbad willingly put himself at the service of the Hunters, offering his great experience in exchange for the rare opportunity to feel the thrill of discovery once again.</p><p>SPECIAL AGENDA (Sherazade, the Weaver of Tales): I'm boastful of knowing every story and legend, and I love to mock those who pride themselves on limited knowledge. I want to ridicule the stories Sherazade tells, highlighting the truths that only I know.</p><p>Sinbad is an invaluable ally IF you can keep him entertained. He knows everything about the world and Broken Tales, can provide information or create helpful Descriptors, and gives +1 Success on checks. However, he gets bored easily - creative and interesting actions are required to capture his attention. The more mundane the situation, the less likely he is to help.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 64, 65","key":"source.sinbad-the-traveler-of-a-thousand-seas","owner":"Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"00b02nqppqn20b00","name":"The Ancient Enemy (Draco the Dragon)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[54]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"El Antiguo Enemigo (Draco el Dragón)","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 54. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Difícil 7","impulse":"To live in solitude and avoid contact with humans, even if deep in my heart I still want to believe that there is a mortal worthy of my respect","oppositionLevel":7}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 54."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"To live in solitude and avoid contact with humans, even if deep in my heart I still want to believe that there is a mortal worthy of my respect","oppositionLevel":7}},"items":[{"_id":"01kh5qu88uq5hk10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","ownerKey":"the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient and powerful creature</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 54","key":"descriptor-principal.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","owner":"The Ancient Enemy (Draco the Dragon)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am an ancient and powerful creature","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01lb4jx55xj4bl10","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","ownerKey":"the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>My body was formed in the fires of creation and common weapons can do nothing against me</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 54","key":"descriptor1-don1.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","owner":"The Ancient Enemy (Draco the Dragon)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"My body was formed in the fires of creation and common weapons can do nothing against me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01f4g093390g4f10","name":"Gift - Colossal Body","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","ownerKey":"the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Cuerpo colosal"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Draco possesses a colossal body and is capable of flying at great speed. During a Scene or Exchange, he can act 3 times instead of once: with his powerful bite, with his front legs, and with his long tail. Draco's strength is so great that each of his actions inflicts 1 additional Wound. Finally, Draco can spit flames from his mouth once per Scene, making an area attack in front of him, engulfing everything in flames.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 54","key":"don1.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","owner":"The Ancient Enemy (Draco the Dragon)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01fefly22ylfef10","name":"Gift - The Power of the Myth","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","ownerKey":"the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: El poder del mito"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Draco is one of the most powerful beings of any myth and, in the course of a Scene, he can use the following powers at will: 1. Shapeshifter: Take on the appearance of an ordinary human or an animal. 2. Magicbreaker: Immediately cancel the effect of a spell or arcane object that has been used in his presence (the user can attempt a Defense Check to avoid the effect of this power). 3. Gift of the Dragon: Shed a piece of his body, such as a scale or a tooth, which can be used to forge objects with extraordinary powers.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 54","key":"don2.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","owner":"The Ancient Enemy (Draco the Dragon)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541843,"modifiedTime":1784372541843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00quiqv66vqiuq00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","ownerKey":"the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 54]<br>49<br>vez por escena, cuando el Insigne pierde su última Herida,<br>se burla del enemigo en un arrebato de ira y saca fuerzas<br>de flaqueza para no caer derribado, recuperando inmedia-<br>tamente 1 Herida.<br>El Antiguo Enemigo<br>Inspirado por el Dragón (neutral)<br>Érase una vez una criatura antigua y poderosa que había<br>sido testigo del desarrollo del mundo desde tiempos inmemo­<br>riales. Los asustados mortales le llamaban Draco, temerosos<br>de su orgulloso porte y su inconmensurable poder. Pero a pe­<br>sar de su temible aspecto, Draco no era malvado, solo curioso.<br>Con la esperanza de crear otro de su especie, como había<br>visto hacer a innumerables mortales, Draco ponía un huevo<br>una vez cada siglo. En cada ocasión, hombres malvados y sin<br>escrúpulos se lo arrebataban antes de que pudiera eclosionar,<br>dejándolo solo. Después de mil años, la desesperación le robó<br>a Draco la aptitud de poner más huevos. La amarga verdad<br>era que poner un huevo significaba condenarlo a un destino<br>malvado. Incluso hoy en día, se dice que Draco sigue espe­<br>rando a una persona con un alma pura, capaz de mostrar la<br>bondad y la compasión suficiente para entibiar su corazón,<br>dándole así esperanza para el futuro. Mientras tanto, las en­<br>gañosas leyendas de un gran dragón, antiguo enemigo de los<br>mortales, se han extendido, reforzadas por historias intere­<br>sadas convertidas en mitos y supersticiones. Cada vez son<br>más los insensatos que buscan la gloria partiendo en busca<br>del Antiguo Enemigo, invocando la gracia de la protección<br>de Dios para dar muerte a la leyenda de una vez por todas.<br>Descriptor: soy una criatura antigua y poderosa. Mi cuer­<br>po se forjó en los fuegos de la creación y las armas comunes<br>no pueden hacer nada contra mí.<br>6 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Objetivo: vivir en soledad y evitar el contacto con los huma­<br>nos, aunque en el fondo de mi corazón siga queriendo creer<br>que hay un mortal digno de mi respeto.<br>Objetivo especial (San Jorge, el Matadragones):<br>odio a San Jorge porque es un símbolo de los que juzgan a<br>los demás ciegamente y están dominados por la fe. Quiero<br>humillarlo y hacer que los que creen en él lo vean como un<br>ser despreciable.<br>Don: Cuerpo colosal. Draco tiene un cuerpo colosal y es<br>capaz de volar a gran velocidad. Durante una escena o un<br>intercambio puede actuar 3 veces en lugar de una: con su<br>poderoso mordisco, sus patas delanteras y su larga cola. La<br>fuerza de Draco es tan grande que cada una de sus acciones<br>inflige 1 Herida adicional. Por último, Draco puede escupir<br>llamas por la boca una vez por escena, realizando un ataque<br>de área frente a él que lo envuelve todo en llamas.<br>Don: El poder del mito. Draco es uno de los seres más<br>poderosos de cualquier mito y, en el transcurso de una<br>escena, puede utilizar los siguientes poderes a voluntad:<br>1. Cambiaformas: adopta la apariencia de un humano<br>corriente o de un animal. 2. Quebrar la magia: cancela<br>inmediatamente el efecto de un hechizo u objeto arcano<br>que se haya utilizado en su presencia (el usuario puede<br>intentar una prueba de defensa para evitar el efecto de este<br>poder). 3. Don del dragón:  desprende un trozo de su<br>cuerpo, como una escama o un diente, que puede utilizarse<br>para forjar objetos con poderes extraordinarios.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there lived an ancient and mighty creature who had been a witness to the world's unfolding since time immemorial. Frightened mortals called it Draco, fearing its proud bearing and immeasurable power. But despite his fearsome appearance, Draco wasn't evil, just curious. In hopes of creating another of his kind, as he had watched countless mortals do, Draco laid an egg once every century. Each time, evil and unscrupulous men took possession of it before it could be hatched, leaving him alone. After a thousand years, despair stole Draco's ability to lay more eggs. The bitter truth was, to lay an egg was to condemn it to an evil fate. Even today, it is said that Draco keeps waiting for a person with a pure soul, able to show kindness and compassion enough to warm his heart, thereby giving him hope for the future. Meanwhile, the lying legends of a great dragon, an ancient Enemy of mortals, have spread, reinforced by self-serving tales grown into myths and superstitions. More and more fools seek glory by setting out in search of the Ancient Enemy, invoking the grace of God's protection, to slay the legend once and for all.</p><p>SPECIAL AGENDA (St. George the Dragon Slayer): I hate St. George because he is a symbol of those who judge others blindly, overawed by faith. I want to humiliate him and make those who believe in him see St. George as the lowest of the low.</p><p>Draco is NOT EVIL - he is a tragic figure seeking someone pure of heart. He can be an incredibly powerful ally if shown kindness and compassion. With 6 Wounds and the ability to act 3 times per turn with +1 Wound per action, plus flame breath, he is nearly unstoppable in combat. His shapeshifting and magic-breaking abilities make him versatile. Approach with respect and kindness, not violence.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 54","key":"source.the-ancient-enemy-draco-the-dragon","owner":"The Ancient Enemy (Draco the Dragon)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01njnld00dlnjn10","name":"The Bremen Musicians (The Haunted Inn)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[68,69]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Los Feroces Músicos de Bremen","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 68, 69. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Feed the fears of the patrons, corrupting their minds so they will revel in the violence that follows","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 68, 69."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Feed the fears of the patrons, corrupting their minds so they will revel in the violence that follows","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"010bpb3ff3bpb010","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","ownerKey":"the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a place full of violence and suffering, able to awaken the deepest fears in the souls of those who approach</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 68, 69","key":"descriptor-principal.the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","owner":"The Bremen Musicians (The Haunted Inn)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a place full of violence and suffering, able to awaken the deepest fears in the souls of those who approach","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01vgj55gg55jgv10","name":"Gift - Cacophony","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","ownerKey":"the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Cacofonía"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Whether it be the words of the Judge, the spells of the Witch, the barking of the Hunter's hound, or the braying of the Monster, the cacophony of horrible noises emitted by the entities inhabiting the Inn is more than enough to make even the sturdiest soul waver. Any action performed inside the Inn during the manifestation of one of its aspects receives a 1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 68, 69","key":"don1.the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","owner":"The Bremen Musicians (The Haunted Inn)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01wahy8dd8yhaw10","name":"Gift - A Past of Suffering","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","ownerKey":"the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Un pasado de sufrimiento"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>When one of the Musicians is hit, the suffering of the Inn's victims overwhelms the attacker, causing cuts and bruises, then forcing them to relive a moment in which they lost something important. Inflicting 1 Wound to one of the Musicians requires a Defense Check in order not to suffer 1 Wound in turn. Once a total of 4 Wounds is inflicted on the Musicians, they quiet down for the rest of the Scene, to regenerate completely in the following one. The only way to truly destroy them is to raze the Inn itself.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 68, 69","key":"don2.the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","owner":"The Bremen Musicians (The Haunted Inn)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01i05q1dd1q50i10","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","ownerKey":"the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 68]<br>63<br>Don: Dádiva de flores. Tras experimentar el amor o la<br>verdadera amistad con una persona, las ramas marchitas de<br>Corazón de Roble florecen, haciendo llover pétalos sobre ella<br>y su nuevo vínculo. Esto genera 3 Contadores de pétalos,<br>cada uno de los cuales puede usarse para curar 1 Herida.<br>Alternativamente, se puede usar 1 pétalo para calmar a al-<br>guien que esté afectado por sentimientos negativos, de modo<br>que pueda ignorar los descriptores y los objetivos relacio-<br>nados con el estado alterado durante el resto de la escena.<br>Los Feroces Músicos<br>de Bremen<br>Inspirados en Los músicos de Bremen<br>(neutral)<br>Presencia oscura de Claudio Serena<br>Cerca de Bremen, en lo más profundo del norte de Alemania,<br>hay una pequeña posada que los viajeros más experimenta­<br>dos recomiendan evitar, llamada Los Músicos. La posada fue<br>el hogar de muchos refugiados y esclavos maltratados por sus<br>amos o que huían de su pasado, ya que era un lugar seguro<br>donde el largo brazo de la ley no podía encontrarlos. Con el<br>tiempo, también ha atraído a bandidos y criminales de la<br>peor calaña, convirtiéndose finalmente en un lugar embruja­<br>do que los viajeros evitan y las madres utilizan para asustar<br>a los niños que no quieren dormir. Desde el vestíbulo princi­<br>pal se oye una cacofonía de ruidos horribles que ningún ser<br>humano podría emitir. Debido a la violencia que ha tenido<br>lugar allí, la posada ha adquirido vida propia, haciendo suyo<br>el dolor y el miedo de todos los que han buscado refugio en<br>ella. Quien se quede, por error o desesperación, se encontrará<br>con uno de los cuatro aspectos que la posada es capaz de ma­nifestar, es decir, los Músicos: la Bruja, siempre seguida por<br>su gato negro; el Cazador, armado con un cuchillo y acompa­ñado por su sabueso; el Juez, cuya pluma de gallo escribe las<br>faltas de quienes se encuentran con su mirada; y el Monstruo,<br>una criatura informe cuyo rebuzno puede llevar a la locura.<br>Descriptor: soy un lugar lleno de violencia y sufrimiento,<br>capaz de despertar los miedos más profundos en las almas de<br>quienes se acercan.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 69]<br>64<br>4 Heridas (1 por Músico)<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: alimentar los miedos de los clientes, corrompiendo<br>su mente para que se deleiten con la violencia generada.<br>Don: Cacofonía. Y a sean las palabras del Juez, los hechizos<br>de la Bruja, los ladridos del sabueso del Cazador o los rebuz-<br>nos del Monstruo, la cacofonía de horribles ruidos emitidos<br>por las entidades que habitan la posada es más que suficiente<br>para hacer vacilar hasta al alma más robusta. Cualquier ac-<br>ción realizada dentro de la posada durante la manifestación<br>de uno de sus aspectos sufre 1 Penalizador.<br>Don: Un pasado de sufrimiento.  Cuando uno de los<br>Músicos es golpeado, el sufrimiento de las víctimas de la po-<br>sada abruma al atacante, causándole cortes y magulladuras,<br>y obligándole a revivir un momento en el que perdió algo<br>importante. Infligir 1 Herida a uno de los Músicos requiere<br>una prueba de defensa para no sufrir también 1 Herida. Una<br>vez que se inflige un total de 4 Heridas a los Músicos, estos<br>se aquietan durante el resto de la escena, para regenerarse<br>completamente en la siguiente. La única forma de destruir-<br>los realmente es arrasar la propia posada.<br>•<br>El Lobo Retornado<br>Inspirado en el Lobo Feroz (oponente)<br>Presencia oscura de Peter Chiykowski<br>En los días en que su corazón aún latía y sus pulmones toda­<br>vía funcionaban, este malvado animal solía merodear por los<br>bosques, evitando al cazador que lo había perseguido durante<br>mucho tiempo por su piel, y acechando en busca de un sabroso<br>bocado entre los viajeros humanos desprevenidos. Imbuido<br>de los poderes de la palabra y la astucia humanas, el lobo<br>engañaba a sus víctimas para que traicionaran a sus seres<br>queridos y que cayeran en sus garras. Se alimentó bien hasta<br>el fatídico día en que se comió a la niña de la caperucita roja<br>y a su abuela. Ese fue el día en que el cazador atrapó y mató<br>al Lobo. A medida que la historia de su muerte se extendía y<br>cambiaba de relato en relato, fue torturado y ejecutado de una<br>docena de formas horripilantes: ahogado en un abrevadero,</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Near Bremen in the deep north of Germany, there is a small Inn that more experienced travelers recommend avoiding, called \"The Musicians\". The Inn was home for many refugees and slaves who were abused by their masters or fleeing their past. It was a safe place where the long arm of the law could not find them. Over time, the Inn has also attracted bandits and criminals of the worst kind, eventually becoming a haunted place that travelers avoid and mothers use to scare children who do not want to sleep. From the main hall, you can hear a cacophony of horrible noises that no human being could produce. Due to the violence that has taken place there, the Inn has acquired a life of its own by making the pain and fear of all those who have sought refuge there its own. Whoever stays, by mistake or desperation, will encounter one of the four aspects that the Inn is able to manifest, namely the Musicians: the Witch, always followed by her black cat; the Hunter, armed with a knife and accompanied by his hound; the Judge, whose cock's feather writes the faults of those who meet his gaze; and the Monster, a shapeless creature whose braying can lead to madness.</p><p>Dark Presence by Claudio Serena.</p><p>The Bremen Musicians is actually a haunted Inn with 4 aspects (1 Wound each): The Witch (with black cat), The Hunter (with hound), The Judge (writes sins with cock feather), and The Monster (maddening braying). All actions inside receive -1 Penalty from Cacophony. Attacking Musicians requires Defense Check or suffer 1 Wound in return. After 4 total Wounds inflicted, they quiet for the Scene but regenerate next Scene. Only destroying the Inn itself permanently stops them.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 68, 69","key":"source.the-bremen-musicians-the-haunted-inn","owner":"The Bremen Musicians (The Haunted Inn)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"014r213uu312r410","name":"The King's Unlikely Tailor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-kings-unlikely-tailor","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[71,72]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"El Insólito Sastre del Rey","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 71, 72. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Fácil 3","impulse":"Finding the purest-hearted person in the nation to make a suit for the King / I fell madly in love with the one person who never asked me for a dress, the King's youngest daughter / I wouldn't spill a drop for her dress, she is too pure / But I know that if I can't find anyone for her father's suit, I'll have to use her","oppositionLevel":3}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 71, 72."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Finding the purest-hearted person in the nation to make a suit for the King / I fell madly in love with the one person who never asked me for a dress, the King's youngest daughter / I wouldn't spill a drop for her dress, she is too pure / But I know that if I can't find anyone for her father's suit, I'll have to use her","oppositionLevel":3}},"items":[{"_id":"00xyn9vnnv9nyx00","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-kings-unlikely-tailor","ownerKey":"the-kings-unlikely-tailor","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an anemic young man with a body covered in scars, escorted and aided by my rich friend who considers me his most precious possession</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 71, 72","key":"descriptor-principal.the-kings-unlikely-tailor","owner":"The King's Unlikely Tailor","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am an anemic young man with a body covered in scars, escorted and aided by my rich friend who considers me his most precious possession","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01xwiie44eiiwx10","name":"Gift - Soul Tailor","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-kings-unlikely-tailor","ownerKey":"the-kings-unlikely-tailor","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Sastre de almas"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A suit sewn by the tailor masks the soul so well that whoever wears it looks like another person. They are seen as admirable and good, even while committing atrocious acts. Only children and the innocents can see beyond the illusion. A Hunter can perform a Defense Check against an Opposition Level Hard 7 to see beyond the deception of Soul Tailor.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 71, 72","key":"don1.the-kings-unlikely-tailor","owner":"The King's Unlikely Tailor","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0006n2h55h2n6000","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-kings-unlikely-tailor","ownerKey":"the-kings-unlikely-tailor","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 71]<br>66<br>El Insólito Sastre del Rey<br>Inspirado en El traje nuevo del emperador (neutral)<br>Presencia oscura de Guido Campanini<br>Érase una vez un joven sastre de provincias con el don de saber ver el alma de las<br>personas para vestirlas de la mejor manera posible. Un día, su mejor amigo le con­<br>venció para que confeccionara un traje para un rico mercader. Para cubrir el alma<br>de lobo del codicioso mercader, el pobre sastre tuvo que utilizar su propia alma,<br>la de un cordero, mezclando su propia sangre en los tintes. Fue un éxito rotundo<br>y el rumor se extendió por todo París. Cuanto más crecía su rica clientela gracias<br>a los rumores difundidos por su amigo, más sangre tenía que derramar el pobre<br>sastre. Su éxito le llevó a la corte del rey, donde el joven sastre comenzó a secues­<br>trar inocentes de todo París para desangrarlos en su taller. Era un paso necesario<br>para fabricar tintes capaces de disfrazar a quienes tenían el alma tan corrompida.<br>Cuando el rey le pidió un traje, el joven sastre se dio cuenta inmediatamente de<br>que la simple sangre no sería suficiente para ocultar todo lo que el hombre había<br>hecho sufrir a su pueblo.<br>Descriptor: soy un joven anémico con el cuerpo cubierto de cicatrices, escoltado<br>y ayudado por mi amigo rico, que me considera su posesión más preciada.<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Fácil 3<br>Objetivo: encontrar a la persona con el corazón más puro del país para ha­<br>cerle un traje al rey. Me enamoré perdidamente de la única persona que nunca<br>me pidió un vestido, la hija menor del rey. No derramaría ni una gota por su<br>vestido, es demasiado pura. Sin embargo, sé que si no encuentro a nadie para<br>el traje de su padre, tendré que utilizarla a ella.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 72]<br>67<br>Don: Sastre de almas. Un traje confeccionado por el<br>Sastre enmascara tan bien el alma que quien lo lleva parece<br>otra persona. Se le considera admirable y bueno, incluso<br>cuando comete actos atroces. Solo los niños y los inocentes<br>pueden ver más allá de la ilusión. Un Cazador puede efec-<br>tuar una prueba de defensa contra un Nivel de Oposición<br>Difícil 7 para ver más allá del engaño del Sastre de almas.<br>El Amigo Tramposo<br>Descriptor: soy el “mejor amigo” del joven sastre y, para<br>mantener mi cómoda vida, estoy dispuesto a hacer cualquier<br>cosa. Cuando actúo en mi propio beneficio, nadie puede<br>detenerme.<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Objetivo: mantener vivo al sastre, hacerme cada vez más<br>rico y utilizar su favor para pedir la mano de la hija del rey.<br>Las Madres<br>del Destino<br>Inspiradas en las hadas madrinas de muchos<br>cuentos (aliadas)<br>Presencia oscura de Francesco Panitti<br>Cloris, Panis y Galis, llamadas las Madres del Destino. Desde<br>el principio de los tiempos, ha habido figuras que controlan el<br>destino de las personas, traman en las sombras y se esconden<br>a plena vista. Acudimos a ellas en busca de consejo y confian­<br>do ciegamente.<br>Mientras tanto, ellas utilizan su proximidad para manipular<br>a la gente, disfrutando de sus intrigas y alegrándose cuando<br>todo sale según sus planes.<br>Estos personajes se representan siempre como tres hermanas<br>que, desde la antigüedad, tejen y cortan los hilos del desti­<br>no de todos. Su verdadera identidad es desconocida, ya que<br>siempre se han ocultado tras el nombre de hadas madrinas.<br>Cuando las tres hermanas se insinúan en las historias que<br>tejen, siempre lo hacen cambiando su apariencia y su nombre<br>para acercarse a los protagonistas y manipularlos según su<br>voluntad. Algunos rumores dicen que es posible hacer tratos<br>con ellas, pero siempre a un precio muy elevado.<br>Descriptor: somos tres hermanas, nunca mostramos nues­<br>tra verdadera identidad, pero retorcemos el destino a nuestro<br>antojo gracias a nuestra poderosa magia.<br>3 Heridas [1 para cada Madre]<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a young provincial tailor with the gift of knowing how to see into people's souls in order to dress them in the best possible manner. One day his best friend convinced him to sew a suit for a wealthy merchant. To cover the wolfish soul of the greedy merchant, the poor tailor had to use his own soul, one of a lamb, mixing his own blood in the dyes. It was a resounding success and the rumor spread all over Paris. The more his wealthy clientele grew thanks to the rumors spread by his friend, the more blood the poor tailor had to shed. His success led him to the King's court, where the young tailor began to kidnap innocents from all over Paris to bleed them in his workshops. It was a necessary step to manufacture dyes capable of disguising those with souls so corrupt. When the King asked for a suit, the young tailor immediately realized that simple blood would not be enough to conceal all the man had done to make his people suffer.</p><p>COMPANION: The Cheating Friend<br>Descriptor: I am the young tailor's 'best' friend and, to keep my life comfortable, I am willing to do anything. When I act for my own benefit, no one can stop me.<br>1 Wound, Opposition Level Hard 7<br>Agenda: Keep the tailor alive, become richer and richer, and to use his favor to ask for the hand of the King's daughter.</p><p>The Tailor's suits magically mask the wearer's soul, making even the most corrupt appear good and admirable. Only children and pure souls see the truth. To create these suits, he must use the blood of innocents. He has fallen in love with the King's daughter (the only pure soul who never asked him for anything), but may be forced to use her blood for the King's suit. Tragic antagonist driven by his manipulative 'friend'.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 71, 72","key":"source.the-kings-unlikely-tailor","owner":"The King's Unlikely Tailor","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"00rfp9h00h9pfr00","name":"The Masked Swashbuckler (Puss in Boots)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[60,61]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"El Espadachín Enmascarado (El Gato con Botas)","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 60, 61. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"To serve my customer without asking questions / Mocking those who trust others too much","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 60, 61."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To serve my customer without asking questions / Mocking those who trust others too much","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"009ftvshhsvtf900","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","ownerKey":"the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a cunning cat who can pretend to be human thanks to a magical mask</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 60, 61","key":"descriptor-principal.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler (Puss in Boots)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am a cunning cat who can pretend to be human thanks to a magical mask","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"008lv2pkkp2vl800","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","ownerKey":"the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I put myself at the service of the highest bidder without qualms</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 60, 61","key":"descriptor1-don1.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler (Puss in Boots)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I put myself at the service of the highest bidder without qualms","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"008vuoejjeouv800","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor2-don2.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","ownerKey":"the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","sequence":3,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 3"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I use my countless lives to get the better of every problem</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 60, 61","key":"descriptor2-don2.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler (Puss in Boots)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I use my countless lives to get the better of every problem","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"011e0k1ii1k0e110","name":"Gift - Nine Lives Like a Cat","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","ownerKey":"the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Nueve vidas como un gato"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Masked Swashbuckler still has eight lives left, so he can return to action once he is eliminated. When he is eliminated, the Storyteller can make him disappear from the current Scene in a blatant way or by revealing his death, even if the Hunters just wanted him disabled. In the following Scene, The Masked Swashbuckler will rejoin the action with the following perks: 1. Once per Scene, he can prevent an enemy from using a Gift he has already seen in action previously. This effect interrupts the target and their action is wasted. 2. His Opposition Level is increased by 1 when defending against an enemy he has already faced in a duel. 3. Once per Scene, he can take advantage of a magical item that he has previously procured to defeat his enemy. The item is disposable and the Storyteller must create a Descriptor to accompany it, such as The Invisibility Potion or The Stone of Blinding Light.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 60, 61","key":"don1.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler (Puss in Boots)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01140ycjjcy04110","name":"Gift - Cat Mask","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","ownerKey":"the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Máscara de gato"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to his magical mask, the Masked Swashbuckler can freely transform between human and cat, taking advantage of this to approach his enemy. The transformation is instantaneous, but it cannot be done in front of witnesses.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 60, 61","key":"don2.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler (Puss in Boots)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"009jyeyrryeyj900","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","ownerKey":"the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 60]<br>55<br>Don: El ritual de los títeres. Comefuego puede animar<br>un títere introduciéndole el alma de un moribundo. A partir<br>de ese momento, el títere está ligado a su creador hasta que<br>este decida liberarlo. Un títere tiene el siguiente perfil:<br>Descriptor: soy un títere animado y hago todo lo que<br>mi creador dice... (ver el don Títere, más abajo).<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Fácil 3<br>Don: Señor de los títeres.  Comefuego siempre está<br>rodeado de al menos 6 títeres. En su presencia, aumenta<br>el Nivel de Oposición de los títeres en 1. Cuando sufre 1<br>Herida, Comefuego puede sacrificar a un títere en lugar de<br>sufrirla.<br>Don: Títere. A cero Heridas el títere se rompe, pero si<br>se repara recupera inmediatamente su Herida y vuelve a la<br>acción. El descriptor de cada títere debe completarse con<br>una característica relacionada con lo que fue en vida. Actuar<br>sobre esa parte del descriptor puede despertar la conciencia<br>dormida del alma enjaulada, permitiendo que el títere actúe<br>independientemente de su señor.<br>El Espadachín<br>Enmascarado<br>Inspirado en El Gato con Botas (oponente)<br>Érase una vez un astuto gato que consiguió que su joven amo<br>amasase una fortuna. No obstante, como suele ocurrir, en lu­<br>gar de agradecerlo, el ahora rico vástago se apresuró a aban­<br>donar a su fiel compañero. Decepcionado, el gato se puso al<br>servicio de otros tres amos, pero una vez alcanzado el éxito y<br>la riqueza, todos se deshicieron de él. Así fue como juró que<br>solo trabajaría para sí mismo. En las aventuras que siguieron,<br>el gato liberó a un antiguo espíritu del que obtuvo un deseo.<br>Al enterarse de este milagro, el desagradecido amo original<br>se presentó, compungido ahora tras desarrollar una rara en­<br>fermedad. Se disculpó, arrepintiéndose de su arrogancia, y<br>pidió al gato que deseara una cura. A cambio, le prometió<br>gratitud eterna. El gato aceptó y pidió el deseo. Sin embargo,<br>tan pronto como se realizó el milagro, el viejo amo del gato lo<br>mató, temeroso de sus increíbles aptitudes.<br>Pero hasta un tonto sabe que los gatos tienen nueve vidas,<br>aunque su amo lo hubiera olvidado. Al día siguiente, el gato<br>regresó de entre los muertos y, enfurecido por la traición, juró<br>vengarse. Se puso una máscara capaz de hacerle parecer hu­<br>mano, lo que le permitió hacerse pasar por un noble duelista,<br>y comenzó a viajar por cortes y salones, vengándose de sus<br>ingratos amos. Después de matarlos uno a uno, el gato desa­<br>rrolló el gusto por la sangre y decidió que, a partir de ese día,<br>su único amo sería el dinero.<br>Descriptor: soy un gato astuto que puede fingir ser humano<br>gracias a una máscara mágica. Me pongo al servicio del mejor<br>postor sin reparos y utilizo mis innumerables vidas para salir<br>airoso de cualquier problema.</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 61]<br>56<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: servir a mi cliente sin hacer preguntas. Burlarme<br>de los que confían demasiado en los demás.<br>Don: Nueve vidas como un gato.  Al Espadachín<br>Enmascarado aún le quedan ocho vidas, por lo que pue-<br>de volver a la acción tras ser eliminado. Tras morir, el<br>Narrador puede hacer que desaparezca de la escena en<br>curso de forma evidente o revelando su muerte, incluso<br>si los Cazadores solo querían incapacitarlo. En la siguien-<br>te escena, se reincorpora a la acción con las siguientes<br>ventajas: 1. Una vez por escena, puede impedir que un<br>enemigo utilice un don que ya ha visto en acción an-<br>teriormente. Este efecto interrumpe al objetivo y su<br>acción se desperdicia. 2. Su Nivel de Oposición se<br>incrementa en 1 cuando se defiende de un enemi-<br>go al que ya se ha enfrentado en un duelo. 3. Una<br>vez por escena, puede aprovechar un objeto mágico<br>que haya conseguido previamente para derrotar a<br>su enemigo. El objeto es desechable y el Narrador<br>debe crear un descriptor que lo acompañe, como<br>poción de invisibilidad o piedra de luz cegadora.<br>Don: Máscara de gato. Gracias a su másca-<br>ra mágica, el Espadachín Enmascarado puede<br>cambiar libremente entre humano y gato, lo<br>que aprovecha para acercarse a su enemigo. La<br>transformación es instantánea, pero no puede<br>realizarla ante testigos.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a cunning Cat who made his young master's fortune. But alas, as often happens, instead of thanking him the now rich scion was quick to abandon his faithful companion. Disappointed, the Cat put himself at the service of three other masters, but once success and wealth were achieved, they all got rid of him. Thus it was that the Cat swore to work only for himself. In the adventures that followed, the Cat released an ancient spirit from which he obtained a wish. Having heard of this miracle, the original ungrateful master showed up, pitiful now after developing a rare disease. He begged for forgiveness, repenting of his arrogance, and asked the Cat to wish for a cure. In return, he promised eternal gratitude. The Cat accepted and made the wish. But, as soon as the miracle was performed the Cat's old master killed him, fearful of his incredible abilities. But even a fool knows that cats have nine lives, though his master might have forgotten. The next day the Cat returned from the dead. Enraged by the betrayal, the Cat swore revenge. He put on a mask capable of making him appear human, allowing him to masquerade as a noble duelist. He began to travel to courts and drawing rooms, taking revenge on his ungrateful masters. After killing them one by one, the Cat developed a taste for blood and decided that from that day on, his only master would be money.</p><p>The Masked Swashbuckler is a mercenary assassin with 9 lives total. When defeated, he returns in the next Scene with enhanced abilities: can cancel enemy Gifts seen before, +1 OL vs previous opponents, and gains a disposable magic item. He can transform between cat and human form. Extremely persistent - killing him once is never enough. Works for the highest bidder without loyalty.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 60, 61","key":"source.the-masked-swashbuckler-puss-in-boots","owner":"The Masked Swashbuckler (Puss in Boots)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"00egjyppppyjge00","name":"The Mothers of Fate (Cloris, Panis, Galis)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[72,73]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"Las Madres del Destino (Cloris, Panis, Galis)","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 72, 73. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Pretending to be friendly and kind, while manipulating others' choices according to our will / Appearing out of nowhere in time of need, thanks to our magic","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 72, 73."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Pretending to be friendly and kind, while manipulating others' choices according to our will / Appearing out of nowhere in time of need, thanks to our magic","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01nt4hqooqh4tn10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","ownerKey":"the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are three sisters, we never show our real identity, but we twist fate to our pleasure thanks to our powerful magic</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 72, 73","key":"descriptor-principal.the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","owner":"The Mothers of Fate (Cloris, Panis, Galis)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"We are three sisters, we never show our real identity, but we twist fate to our pleasure thanks to our powerful magic","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00uxmx2vv2xmxu00","name":"Gift - The Way Forward","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","ownerKey":"the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: El camino a seguir"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The knowledge of the three sisters is absolute and unlimited; they know the past, present, and future. By asking the Mothers of Fate for advice or information, you will be able to obtain guidance to follow to achieve your goals or information that few know. This all comes at a high price. Once per Session you can ask the Storyteller a direct question about a person, a place, or a secret, to which they will answer in detail and with specifics. In exchange, the Hunter must perform a task for the Mothers, but which the Hunter will not remember. The Hunter receives 1 Pact Token, which the Storyteller can spend during a Scene to introduce the effects of the action the Hunter performed for the Mothers. The action can be anything, even in open contrast to the Hunter's moral stances. They will be aware of what they have done only when the truth is revealed.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 72, 73","key":"don1.the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","owner":"The Mothers of Fate (Cloris, Panis, Galis)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00v7miruurim7v00","name":"Gift - As if by Magic","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","ownerKey":"the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Como por arte de magia"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The power of the Mothers of Fate is such that it can change reality for a short period of time. By unconditionally accepting a request from the Mothers of Fate and spending 1 Soma, once per Session, the Hunter can ask the Mothers to modify the surrounding environment, adding or removing any object, creating an advantage for themselves or whoever they wish.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 72, 73","key":"don2.the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","owner":"The Mothers of Fate (Cloris, Panis, Galis)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00m39snmmns93m00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","ownerKey":"the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 72]<br>67<br>Don: Sastre de almas. Un traje confeccionado por el<br>Sastre enmascara tan bien el alma que quien lo lleva parece<br>otra persona. Se le considera admirable y bueno, incluso<br>cuando comete actos atroces. Solo los niños y los inocentes<br>pueden ver más allá de la ilusión. Un Cazador puede efec-<br>tuar una prueba de defensa contra un Nivel de Oposición<br>Difícil 7 para ver más allá del engaño del Sastre de almas.<br>El Amigo Tramposo<br>Descriptor: soy el “mejor amigo” del joven sastre y, para<br>mantener mi cómoda vida, estoy dispuesto a hacer cualquier<br>cosa. Cuando actúo en mi propio beneficio, nadie puede<br>detenerme.<br>1 Herida<br>Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Objetivo: mantener vivo al sastre, hacerme cada vez más<br>rico y utilizar su favor para pedir la mano de la hija del rey.<br>Las Madres<br>del Destino<br>Inspiradas en las hadas madrinas de muchos<br>cuentos (aliadas)<br>Presencia oscura de Francesco Panitti<br>Cloris, Panis y Galis, llamadas las Madres del Destino. Desde<br>el principio de los tiempos, ha habido figuras que controlan el<br>destino de las personas, traman en las sombras y se esconden<br>a plena vista. Acudimos a ellas en busca de consejo y confian­<br>do ciegamente.<br>Mientras tanto, ellas utilizan su proximidad para manipular<br>a la gente, disfrutando de sus intrigas y alegrándose cuando<br>todo sale según sus planes.<br>Estos personajes se representan siempre como tres hermanas<br>que, desde la antigüedad, tejen y cortan los hilos del desti­<br>no de todos. Su verdadera identidad es desconocida, ya que<br>siempre se han ocultado tras el nombre de hadas madrinas.<br>Cuando las tres hermanas se insinúan en las historias que<br>tejen, siempre lo hacen cambiando su apariencia y su nombre<br>para acercarse a los protagonistas y manipularlos según su<br>voluntad. Algunos rumores dicen que es posible hacer tratos<br>con ellas, pero siempre a un precio muy elevado.<br>Descriptor: somos tres hermanas, nunca mostramos nues­<br>tra verdadera identidad, pero retorcemos el destino a nuestro<br>antojo gracias a nuestra poderosa magia.<br>3 Heridas [1 para cada Madre]<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 73]<br>68<br>Objetivo: fingir amistad y amabilidad, mientras manipu­<br>lamos las decisiones de los demás de acuerdo con nuestra<br>voluntad. Usar nuestra magia para aparecer de la nada en<br>momentos de necesidad.<br>Don: El camino a seguir. El saber de las tres hermanas es<br>absoluto e ilimitado; conocen el pasado, el presente y el futu-<br>ro. Al pedir consejo o información a las Madres del Destino,<br>se obtiene una guía a seguir para lograr los objetivos o infor-<br>mación que pocos conocen. Todo esto tiene un alto precio.<br>Una vez por sesión, puedes hacer una pregunta directa al<br>Narrador sobre una persona, un lugar o un secreto, a lo que<br>responderá con detalle y de forma específica. A cambio, el<br>Cazador debe realizar una tarea para las Madres, pero que<br>no recordará. El Cazador obtiene 1 Contador de pacto, que<br>el Narrador puede gastar durante una escena para introdu-<br>cir los efectos de la acción que el Cazador realizó para las<br>Madres. La acción puede ser cualquier cosa e incluso estar<br>en abierto contraste con las posiciones morales del Cazador.<br>Solo será consciente de lo que ha hecho cuando se revele la<br>verdad.<br>Don: Como por arte de magia. El poder de las Madres<br>del Destino es tal que puede cambiar la realidad durante un<br>breve periodo de tiempo. Aceptando incondicionalmente<br>una petición de las Madres del Destino y gastando 1 Soma,<br>una vez por sesión, el Cazador puede pedir a las Madres que<br>modifiquen el entorno circundante, añadiendo o quitando<br>cualquier objeto, creando una ventaja para sí mismo o para<br>quien quiera.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Cloris, Panis, and Galis, called the Mothers of Fate. Since the dawn of time, there have been figures who control people's destiny, plot in the shadows, and hide in plain sight. They are the ones we go to for advice and whom we trust blindly. They use their proximity to manipulate people, enjoying their intrigues and rejoicing when everything goes according to their plans. These figures are always represented as three sisters who, since ancient times, have been weaving and cutting the threads of everyone's destiny. Their true identity is unknown as they have always hidden behind the name of Fairy Godmothers. When the three sisters insinuate themselves into the stories they wove, they always did so by changing their appearance and name, all to get closer to the protagonists and manipulate them according to their will. Some rumors say that it is possible to make deals with them, but always at a very high price.</p><p>Dark Presence by Francesco Panitti.</p><p>The Mothers of Fate are 3 sisters (1 Wound each, 3 total) who manipulate destiny itself. Their gifts are incredibly powerful but dangerous:<br>- The Way Forward: Ask any question, get complete answer, but you unknowingly perform a task for them (Pact Token). The Storyteller reveals what you did later - could be anything, even against your morals.<br>- As if by Magic: Spend 1 Soma to alter reality (add/remove objects) if you accept their request.</p><p>They appear as helpful Fairy Godmothers but are master manipulators weaving fate to their designs. Never show their true identity.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 72, 73","key":"source.the-mothers-of-fate-cloris-panis-galis","owner":"The Mothers of Fate (Cloris, Panis, Galis)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"00nyekffffkeyn00","name":"The Periwinkle Peer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-periwinkle-peer","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[53,54]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"El Insigne Azul Lavanda","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 53, 54. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"I must prove my perfection, even if it means drowning doubters in blood","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 53, 54."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I must prove my perfection, even if it means drowning doubters in blood","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00ko5zzggzz5ok00","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-periwinkle-peer","ownerKey":"the-periwinkle-peer","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the best at everything I do and I must win every challenge</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 53, 54","key":"descriptor-principal.the-periwinkle-peer","owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am the best at everything I do and I must win every challenge","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00li4t2dd2t4il00","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.the-periwinkle-peer","ownerKey":"the-periwinkle-peer","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I do not excel in science and academic knowledge, but no one must discover this weakness of mine</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 53, 54","key":"descriptor1-don1.the-periwinkle-peer","owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I do not excel in science and academic knowledge, but no one must discover this weakness of mine","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00l857deed758l00","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor2-don2.the-periwinkle-peer","ownerKey":"the-periwinkle-peer","sequence":3,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 3"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I prefer to show off my physical prowess and skill</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 53, 54","key":"descriptor2-don2.the-periwinkle-peer","owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I prefer to show off my physical prowess and skill","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00rbhavffvahbr00","name":"Gift - Obsession for Perfection","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-periwinkle-peer","ownerKey":"the-periwinkle-peer","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Obsesión por la perfección"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Periwinkle Peer draws strength from the drive to win every challenge. When an enemy succeeds in a Defense Check against his action, the Peer gets +1 to his Opposition Level for the rest of the Scene. This bonus is cumulative. Once per Scene, when the Peer receives his final Wound, he will mock his enemy in a fit of rage and grit his teeth to keep from being knocked out, immediately recovering 1 Wound.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 53, 54","key":"don1.the-periwinkle-peer","owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00rlgwkeekwglr00","name":"Gift - Divine Charm","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-periwinkle-peer","ownerKey":"the-periwinkle-peer","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Encanto divino"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Periwinkle Peer possesses good looks and charm out of the ordinary. With his mere presence, he is able to beguile anyone. During a Scene in which he is present, the Storyteller can create an Agenda for a Minor NPC that describes their infatuation with the Peer. This Agenda is more important than all of the NPC's past ties, and also any pacts they might have struck with the Hunters. The Peer can also influence Major NPCs (at the Storyteller's discretion) or a Hunter. In this case, the Player will create a Descriptor that represents how The Periwinkle Peer impressed the Hunter. This new Descriptor lasts until the next Interlude and can be marked as usual to get XP.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 53, 54","key":"don2.the-periwinkle-peer","owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00k1hokeekoh1k00","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-periwinkle-peer","ownerKey":"the-periwinkle-peer","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 53]<br>48<br>El Insigne Azul<br>Lavanda<br>Inspirado en el Príncipe Azul (oponente)<br>Érase una vez un apuesto noble que había nacido como he­<br>redero de una familia rica. El joven señor era famoso por<br>su preciada capa de color azul lavanda, que atraía todas las<br>miradas al entrar en cualquier lugar. Pero a pesar de la ad­<br>miración de todos y de que todas las jóvenes le reclamaban<br>como amante, el joven señor estaba obsesionado con<br>una sola cosa: la perfección. Sus padres eran los<br>únicos que conocían tal obsesión, que en el pasado<br>le había llevado a matar a su hermano, ejecu­<br>tado por el delito de ser mejor jinete. Cegados<br>por el amor, los padres del joven señor le pre­<br>sionaron para que siguiera la carrera militar.<br>El joven señor ascendió rápidamente en el<br>escalafón, motivado como siempre por<br>sobresalir. Pero entonces descubrió las<br>sórdidas intrigas que se podían utili­<br>zar para conseguir favores y ascen­<br>sos. Su locura resurgió, llevándolo<br>al asesinato una vez más. En la<br>actualidad, el joven señor, fugi­<br>tivo y desertor, deambula sin ce­<br>sar, siempre en busca de desafíos<br>para demostrar su superioridad<br>y prestando servicio a cualquiera<br>que alabe su perfección.<br>Descriptor:  soy el mejor en<br>todo lo que hago y debo ganar<br>cualquier desafío. No destaco en<br>los conocimientos científicos y académicos, pero nadie debe<br>descubrir tal debilidad. Prefiero demostrar mi destreza física<br>y adiestramiento.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: debo demostrar mi perfección, aunque signifique<br>bañar en sangre a los que dudan.<br>Don: Encanto divino.  El Insigne Azul Lavanda goza de<br>una apariencia y un encanto fuera de lo común. Con su<br>sola presencia, es capaz de seducir a cualquiera. Durante<br>una escena en la que esté presente, el Narrador puede crear<br>un objetivo para un PNJ menor que describa su flechazo<br>con el Insigne. Este objetivo es más importante que todos<br>los vínculos pasados del PNJ, y también que cual -<br>quier pacto que haya hecho con los Cazadores.<br>También puede influir en los PNJs principales<br>(a discreción del Narrador) o en un Cazador.<br>En este caso, el jugador crea un descriptor<br>que represente cómo ha impresionado<br>al Cazador. Este nuevo descriptor<br>dura hasta el siguiente interludio y<br>puede ser marcado como de cos -<br>tumbre para obtener PX.<br>Don: Obsesión por la perfec-<br>ción. El Insigne Azul Lavanda ob-<br>tiene su fuerza del afán por vencer<br>en cualquier desafío. Cuando un<br>enemigo tiene éxito en una prueba<br>de defensa contra su acción, ob-<br>tiene +1 a su Nivel de Oposición<br>durante el resto de la escena. Esta<br>bonificación es acumulativa. Una</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 54]<br>49<br>vez por escena, cuando el Insigne pierde su última Herida,<br>se burla del enemigo en un arrebato de ira y saca fuerzas<br>de flaqueza para no caer derribado, recuperando inmedia-<br>tamente 1 Herida.<br>El Antiguo Enemigo<br>Inspirado por el Dragón (neutral)<br>Érase una vez una criatura antigua y poderosa que había<br>sido testigo del desarrollo del mundo desde tiempos inmemo­<br>riales. Los asustados mortales le llamaban Draco, temerosos<br>de su orgulloso porte y su inconmensurable poder. Pero a pe­<br>sar de su temible aspecto, Draco no era malvado, solo curioso.<br>Con la esperanza de crear otro de su especie, como había<br>visto hacer a innumerables mortales, Draco ponía un huevo<br>una vez cada siglo. En cada ocasión, hombres malvados y sin<br>escrúpulos se lo arrebataban antes de que pudiera eclosionar,<br>dejándolo solo. Después de mil años, la desesperación le robó<br>a Draco la aptitud de poner más huevos. La amarga verdad<br>era que poner un huevo significaba condenarlo a un destino<br>malvado. Incluso hoy en día, se dice que Draco sigue espe­<br>rando a una persona con un alma pura, capaz de mostrar la<br>bondad y la compasión suficiente para entibiar su corazón,<br>dándole así esperanza para el futuro. Mientras tanto, las en­<br>gañosas leyendas de un gran dragón, antiguo enemigo de los<br>mortales, se han extendido, reforzadas por historias intere­<br>sadas convertidas en mitos y supersticiones. Cada vez son<br>más los insensatos que buscan la gloria partiendo en busca<br>del Antiguo Enemigo, invocando la gracia de la protección<br>de Dios para dar muerte a la leyenda de una vez por todas.<br>Descriptor: soy una criatura antigua y poderosa. Mi cuer­<br>po se forjó en los fuegos de la creación y las armas comunes<br>no pueden hacer nada contra mí.<br>6 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Objetivo: vivir en soledad y evitar el contacto con los huma­<br>nos, aunque en el fondo de mi corazón siga queriendo creer<br>que hay un mortal digno de mi respeto.<br>Objetivo especial (San Jorge, el Matadragones):<br>odio a San Jorge porque es un símbolo de los que juzgan a<br>los demás ciegamente y están dominados por la fe. Quiero<br>humillarlo y hacer que los que creen en él lo vean como un<br>ser despreciable.<br>Don: Cuerpo colosal. Draco tiene un cuerpo colosal y es<br>capaz de volar a gran velocidad. Durante una escena o un<br>intercambio puede actuar 3 veces en lugar de una: con su<br>poderoso mordisco, sus patas delanteras y su larga cola. La<br>fuerza de Draco es tan grande que cada una de sus acciones<br>inflige 1 Herida adicional. Por último, Draco puede escupir<br>llamas por la boca una vez por escena, realizando un ataque<br>de área frente a él que lo envuelve todo en llamas.<br>Don: El poder del mito. Draco es uno de los seres más<br>poderosos de cualquier mito y, en el transcurso de una<br>escena, puede utilizar los siguientes poderes a voluntad:<br>1. Cambiaformas: adopta la apariencia de un humano<br>corriente o de un animal. 2. Quebrar la magia: cancela<br>inmediatamente el efecto de un hechizo u objeto arcano<br>que se haya utilizado en su presencia (el usuario puede<br>intentar una prueba de defensa para evitar el efecto de este<br>poder). 3. Don del dragón:  desprende un trozo de su<br>cuerpo, como una escama o un diente, que puede utilizarse<br>para forjar objetos con poderes extraordinarios.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a handsome nobleman born the heir to a wealthy family. The Young Lord was famous for his prized, periwinkle blue cloak, which would catch every eye whenever he entered a room. But despite everyone's admiration and every young woman claiming him as a lover, the lordling was obsessed with only one thing: perfection. The Young Lord's parents were the only ones who knew of their son's bedeviling compulsion, which in the past had driven him to kill his brother, executed for the crime of being a better horseman. Blinded by love, the Young Lord's parents pushed him into a military career. The Young Lord rose through the ranks quickly, driven as he ever was to excel. Then, he learned of sordid intrigues that could be used to garner preferment and promotion. His madness resurfaced, eventually driving him to murder once more. A wanted man and a deserter, today the Young Lord wanders endlessly, always looking for challenges to prove his superiority, putting himself at the service of anyone who praises his perfection.</p><p>The Periwinkle Peer is a dangerous sociopath driven by an obsession with perfection. His Obsession for Perfection gift makes him progressively more dangerous as the fight continues, and he can recover from what should be his final wound. His Divine Charm makes him incredibly manipulative, able to turn NPCs and even Hunters against each other. Be careful engaging with him - flattery will draw his attention, but criticism might trigger murderous rage.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 53, 54","key":"source.the-periwinkle-peer","owner":"The Periwinkle Peer","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01ru18b77b81ur10","name":"The Returning Wolf","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-returning-wolf","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[69,70]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"El Lobo Retornado","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 69, 70. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"I am hell-bent on revenge on the human world / I am a revenant animated by undying acrimony for the soft-skinned creatures that invaded my woods and yet had the audacity to condemn me to death / My only goal now is to glut my endless hunger for human flesh and fear / I have a particular hatred for children, the elderly, and Hunters, whom I see as responsible for my many deaths","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 69, 70."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am hell-bent on revenge on the human world / I am a revenant animated by undying acrimony for the soft-skinned creatures that invaded my woods and yet had the audacity to condemn me to death / My only goal now is to glut my endless hunger for human flesh and fear / I have a particular hatred for children, the elderly, and Hunters, whom I see as responsible for my many deaths","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01xs68eqqe86sx10","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-returning-wolf","ownerKey":"the-returning-wolf","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the Returning Wolf: I am bad, hungry, and now I am the hunter</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 69, 70","key":"descriptor-principal.the-returning-wolf","owner":"The Returning Wolf","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am the Returning Wolf: I am bad, hungry, and now I am the hunter","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541844,"modifiedTime":1784372541844,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"007ww4vppv4ww700","name":"Gift - Frightening Revenant","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-returning-wolf","ownerKey":"the-returning-wolf","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Resucitado aterrador"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Wolf reveals horrific mutilations, each revealing something about his deaths. His empty eyes are as cold and bottomless as the well he was drowned in. His pelt is a patchwork of burns and skinned flesh. His belly is full of slashes and stitches. His growl is a terrifying sound, grinding painfully from a chest full of heavy stones and broken bones. No NPCs will approach or fight the Wolf, being paralyzed by terror. Particularly powerful NPCs, at the Storyteller's discretion, can ignore this effect. When a Hunter acts against the Returning Wolf, they suffer 1 Penalty for each action taken.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 69, 70","key":"don1.the-returning-wolf","owner":"The Returning Wolf","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0072xbssssbx2700","name":"Gift - The Better to Eat You With","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-returning-wolf","ownerKey":"the-returning-wolf","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Para comerte mejor"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Wolf can swallow his enemies whole, trapping them inside his belly and crushing them to death with the heavy stones the grandmother sewed inside it. When the Returning Wolf inflicts 1 Wound, it can swallow the victim whole as an additional effect. In the next action, the victim can only try to free themselves. If they fail the Position Check, or if they decide to stay in the belly of the Returning Wolf, they receive 1 additional Wound.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 69, 70","key":"don2.the-returning-wolf","owner":"The Returning Wolf","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"002uye1kk1eyu200","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-returning-wolf","ownerKey":"the-returning-wolf","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 69]<br>64<br>4 Heridas (1 por Músico)<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: alimentar los miedos de los clientes, corrompiendo<br>su mente para que se deleiten con la violencia generada.<br>Don: Cacofonía. Y a sean las palabras del Juez, los hechizos<br>de la Bruja, los ladridos del sabueso del Cazador o los rebuz-<br>nos del Monstruo, la cacofonía de horribles ruidos emitidos<br>por las entidades que habitan la posada es más que suficiente<br>para hacer vacilar hasta al alma más robusta. Cualquier ac-<br>ción realizada dentro de la posada durante la manifestación<br>de uno de sus aspectos sufre 1 Penalizador.<br>Don: Un pasado de sufrimiento.  Cuando uno de los<br>Músicos es golpeado, el sufrimiento de las víctimas de la po-<br>sada abruma al atacante, causándole cortes y magulladuras,<br>y obligándole a revivir un momento en el que perdió algo<br>importante. Infligir 1 Herida a uno de los Músicos requiere<br>una prueba de defensa para no sufrir también 1 Herida. Una<br>vez que se inflige un total de 4 Heridas a los Músicos, estos<br>se aquietan durante el resto de la escena, para regenerarse<br>completamente en la siguiente. La única forma de destruir-<br>los realmente es arrasar la propia posada.<br>•<br>El Lobo Retornado<br>Inspirado en el Lobo Feroz (oponente)<br>Presencia oscura de Peter Chiykowski<br>En los días en que su corazón aún latía y sus pulmones toda­<br>vía funcionaban, este malvado animal solía merodear por los<br>bosques, evitando al cazador que lo había perseguido durante<br>mucho tiempo por su piel, y acechando en busca de un sabroso<br>bocado entre los viajeros humanos desprevenidos. Imbuido<br>de los poderes de la palabra y la astucia humanas, el lobo<br>engañaba a sus víctimas para que traicionaran a sus seres<br>queridos y que cayeran en sus garras. Se alimentó bien hasta<br>el fatídico día en que se comió a la niña de la caperucita roja<br>y a su abuela. Ese fue el día en que el cazador atrapó y mató<br>al Lobo. A medida que la historia de su muerte se extendía y<br>cambiaba de relato en relato, fue torturado y ejecutado de una<br>docena de formas horripilantes: ahogado en un abrevadero,</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 70]<br>65<br>hervido en una olla, aplastado en el suelo, partido por la mi­<br>tad o abierto en canal y con el vientre lleno de pesadas piedras.<br>Los numerosos relatos sangraron juntos y el Lobo, destrozado<br>por innumerables manos y condenado por innumerables len­<br>guas, ha regresado para reclamar venganza por cada muerte<br>a la que fue sometido. Es todo lo que se ha dicho de él: grande,<br>feroz y sediento de sangre.<br>Descriptor: soy el Lobo Retornado: soy feroz, tengo hambre<br>y ahora yo soy el cazador.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5<br>Objetivo: estoy empeñado en vengarme del mundo humano.<br>He resucitado animado por un rencor eterno hacia las cria­<br>turas de piel blanda que invadieron mi bosque y tuvieron la<br>audacia de condenarme a muerte. Mi único objetivo es saciar<br>mi interminable hambre de carne humana y de miedo. Siento<br>un odio especial por los niños, los ancianos y los cazadores,<br>a quienes considero responsables de mis numerosas muertes.<br>Objetivo especial (Iskra, la Joven Loba):  albergo un<br>profundo odio por esta alimaña. Está unida a mi dolor. Quiero<br>devorarla y dejar que muera lentamente en mi estómago.<br>Nota: Iskra, la Joven Loba, es una de las Cazadoras que<br>aparecen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.<br>Objetivo especial (Garou, el Viejo Lobo): quiero adver­<br>tir a ese pobre tonto para que entienda a qué se enfrentará si<br>sigue al lado de esos malditos humanos.<br>Don: Para comerte mejor. El Lobo puede tragarse a sus<br>enemigos enteros, atrapándolos en su vientre y aplastándo-<br>los hasta la muerte con las pesadas piedras que la abuela<br>cosió en su interior. Cuando el Lobo Retornado inflige 1<br>Herida, puede tragarse a la víctima entera como efecto adi-<br>cional. En la siguiente acción, la víctima solo puede intentar<br>liberarse. Si falla la prueba de posición, o si decide quedarse<br>en el vientre del Lobo Retornado, sufre 1 Herida adicional.<br>Don: Resucitado aterrador. El Lobo manifiesta horri-<br>bles mutilaciones, cada una de las cuales revela algo sobre<br>sus muertes. Sus ojos vacíos son tan fríos y sin fondo como<br>el pozo en el que se ahogó. Su pelaje es un mosaico de que-<br>maduras y carne desollada. Su vientre está lleno de cortes y<br>puntos. Su gruñido es un sonido aterrador, que sale dolo-<br>rosamente de un pecho lleno de pesadas piedras y huesos<br>rotos. Ningún PNJ se acerca al Lobo ni lucha contra él, ya<br>que queda paralizado por el terror. Los PNJs especialmente<br>poderosos, a discreción del Narrador, pueden ignorar este<br>efecto. Cuando un Cazador actúa contra el Lobo Retornado,<br>sufre 1 Penalizador en todas las acciones.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>In the days when his heart still beat and his lungs still drew breath, this wicked animal used to prowl the woods, avoiding the huntsman who had long hunted him for his pelt, and stalking for a tasty bite amongst unsuspecting human travelers. Imbued with the powers of human speech and cunning, the wolf tricked his victims into betraying their loved ones into his clutches as well. He fed well until the fateful day he ate up the little girl in the red hood and her grandmother. That was the day the huntsman caught and slew the Wolf. As the story of his death spread and changed from telling to telling, he was tortured and executed in a dozen gruesome ways: drowned in a trough, boiled in a pot, smashed into the ground, cut down, cut open and his belly filled with heavy stones. The many tellings bled together and the Wolf, mangled by countless hands and condemned by countless tongues, has returned to claim revenge for every death he was subjected to. He is everything that has been said about him. Big. Bad. And out for blood.</p><p>Dark Presence by Peter Chiykowski.</p><p>SPECIAL AGENDAS:<br>- Iskra the Young Wolf: I harbor a deep hatred for this little pest. She is somewhat linked to my pain. I want to swallow her and let her slowly die in my stomach.<br>- Garou the Old Wolf: I want to warn the poor fool so that he understands what he will face if he keeps by the side of these blasted humans.</p><p>The Returning Wolf is a revenant embodying every gruesome death from folklore. NPCs won't fight him (terror). Hunters get -1 Penalty per action. Can swallow victims whole - trapped victims take 1 additional Wound next turn if they don't escape. Terrifying opponent with special hatred for children, elderly, and Hunters.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 69, 70","key":"source.the-returning-wolf","owner":"The Returning Wolf","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01j51w5vv5w15j10","name":"The Silent (The Mermaid Assassin)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[56,57]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"La Silenciosa (La Asesina Sirena)","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 56, 57. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"I work for anyone who can afford to pay with magic and arcane items, which I intend to use to become a Mermaid again","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 56, 57."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I work for anyone who can afford to pay with magic and arcane items, which I intend to use to become a Mermaid again","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00vea2hssh2aev00","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","ownerKey":"the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an unscrupulous killer, I hate humanity and the body to which I am condemned</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 56, 57","key":"descriptor-principal.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","owner":"The Silent (The Mermaid Assassin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am an unscrupulous killer, I hate humanity and the body to which I am condemned","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00w88vkppkv88w00","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","ownerKey":"the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>My voice is reduced to a faint whisper, which weakened my Siren powers but did not take them away</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 56, 57","key":"descriptor1-don1.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","owner":"The Silent (The Mermaid Assassin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"My voice is reduced to a faint whisper, which weakened my Siren powers but did not take them away","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01pz1v0nn0v1zp10","name":"Gift - The Siren's Whisper","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","ownerKey":"the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: El susurro de la sirena"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Silent has given away her voice, but she can still whisper. Any opponent acting against the Silent must pass a Defense Check before taking their action, or be dazed and miss the opportunity to act. A target cannot be affected by this Gift more than once per Scene.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 56, 57","key":"don1.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","owner":"The Silent (The Mermaid Assassin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01q91gpmmpg19q10","name":"Gift - The Siren's Charm","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","ownerKey":"the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: El encanto de la sirena"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Silent possesses an otherworldly beauty that can awaken the lustful desire of those around her. Once per Scene, if the Silent wants, every subject in her presence will receive the Descriptor: I desire the Silent with all my heart and would do anything to have her. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to resist. Particularly powerful NPCs, at the discretion of the Storyteller, may not succumb to the Siren's Charm.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 56, 57","key":"don2.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","owner":"The Silent (The Mermaid Assassin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"011p4lmqqml4p110","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","ownerKey":"the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 56]<br>51<br>Objetivo: derrotar a los Cazadores de la Orden y encontrar<br>a Elisa. Salvar a Elisa de las garras de la Orden, aunque sig­<br>nifique su destrucción.<br>Objetivo especial (Morgana del Lago):  hemos descu­<br>bierto que todo lo que nos ha pasado es culpa de la bruja<br>Morgana, así que queremos secuestrarla y obligarla a salvar<br>a Elisa con su magia.<br>Nota: Morgana del Lago es una de las Cazadoras que apa-<br>recen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.<br>Don: Convertirse en cisne. Un miembro de la Banda de<br>los Cisnes Salvajes puede transformarse en cisne a volun-<br>tad. La transformación es inmediata. Cuando ocurre, le da<br>el nuevo descriptor: soy un cisne salvaje, puedo volar, pero<br>mantengo mi conciencia humana. La ropa, los objetos y otras<br>pertenencias del miembro de la banda no se pierden durante<br>la transformación.<br>Don: Bandada de cisnes.  Cuando un miembro de la<br>banda actúa y tiene al menos un compañero que le apoya,<br>aumenta su Nivel de Oposición en 1. Si al menos tres miem-<br>bros se concentran en apoyar la misma acción, quien la lleva<br>a cabo aumenta su Nivel de Oposición en 3 puntos.<br>La Silenciosa<br>Inspirada en La sirenita (oponente)<br>Érase una vez una joven sirena que fue capturada por un<br>pescador. Al percibir su valor, el codicioso pescador la entregó<br>como tributo al noble local, que la exhibió como un animal<br>exótico, fascinando a todo el mundo, pero especialmente a su<br>hijo. Con el tiempo, el joven aristócrata empezó a mirar a la<br>sirena con otros ojos, y su curiosidad se convirtió en pasión.<br>Ambos consumaron un deseo prohibido, que llevó a la joven<br>sirena a sentir un amor sincero por su príncipe. El sentimien­<br>to, por desgracia, no fue correspondido. En cuanto se presentó<br>la oportunidad, el hijo del noble abandonó la casa familiar<br>para casarse. La sirena fue vendida a un circo, destinada a<br>terminar sus días como monstruo de feria, asustando a los<br>necios con su miseria. El encuentro con una misteriosa bruja<br>llamada Marina cambió su destino. A cambio de su voz, ob­<br>tuvo una poción para cambiar de forma.<br>—Ten cuidado —dijo la bruja—. ¿De verdad quieres renun­<br>ciar a lo que eres para perseguir un amor fugaz?<br>La sirena no se lo pensó dos veces y se bebió la poción para<br>ser completamente humana. Volvió con su príncipe, solo para<br>descubrir que él apenas se acordaba de ella y del tiempo que<br>habían pasado juntos. El corazón de la sirena se ensombreció.<br>En una noche de luna llena, bebió la sangre de su amor per­<br>dido, además de la de toda su nueva familia.<br>Descriptor: soy una asesina sin escrúpulos, odio a la huma­<br>nidad y el cuerpo al que estoy condenada. Mi voz se reduce a<br>un débil susurro, lo que ha debilitado mis poderes de sirena,<br>pero no me los ha quitado.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 57]<br>52<br>Objetivo: trabajo para quien pueda pagar con objetos mági­<br>cos y arcanos, que pienso utilizar para volver a ser una sirena.<br>Objetivo especial (Marina, la Exploradora del<br>Mar): odio a Marina por lo que me hizo. Aunque me ad­<br>virtió de lo que pasaría, su poder puede arruinar la vida de<br>la gente. Quiero que me convierta en una sirena de nuevo<br>antes de matarla.<br>Don: El encanto de la sirena.  La Silenciosa tiene una<br>belleza de otro mundo que puede despertar el deseo lu-<br>jurioso de los que la rodean. Una vez por escena, si la<br>Silenciosa quiere, todo sujeto en su presencia sufre el des-<br>criptor deseo a la Silenciosa con todo mi corazón y haría<br>cualquier cosa por tenerla. Un Cazador puede intentar una<br>prueba de defensa para resistirse. Los PNJs especialmente<br>poderosos, a discreción del Narrador, pueden resistirse al<br>encanto de la sirena.<br>Don: El susurro de la sirena. La Silenciosa ha renuncia-<br>do a su voz, pero aún puede susurrar. Cualquier oponente<br>que actúe contra ella debe superar una prueba de defensa<br>antes de realizar su acción, o queda aturdido y pierde la<br>oportunidad de actuar. Un sujeto no puede ser afectado<br>por este don más de una vez por escena.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there was a young Mermaid who was captured by a fisherman. Sensing her worth, the greedy fisherman gave the Mermaid as a tribute to the local nobleman. He displayed her as an exotic animal, fascinating everyone, but particularly the nobleman's son. Over time, the young man began to look at the Mermaid with different eyes, and his curiosity turned into passion. The young Mermaid was consumed by a forbidden desire, which led her to feel sincere love for her prince. The feeling was, unfortunately, not reciprocated. As soon as the opportunity arose, the nobleman's son left the family home to get married. The Mermaid was sold to a circus, destined to end her days as a sideshow monster frightening fools with her misery. The meeting with a mysterious witch named Marina changed her destiny. In exchange for her voice, she obtained a shapeshifting potion. \"Be careful,\" said the witch. \"Do you really wish to give up what you are to pursue a fleeting love?\" The Mermaid didn't think twice about it and drank the potion to become fully human. She returned to her prince only to find that he barely remembered her and their time together. The Mermaid's heart darkened. On a full moon night, she drank the blood of her lost love, and with it that of his entire new family.</p><p>SPECIAL AGENDA (Marina the Sea Explorer): I hate Marina for what she did to me. Even though she warned me about what would happen, her power can ruin people's lives. I want her to make me a Mermaid again before I kill her.</p><p>The Silent is a tragic assassin-for-hire. Her Siren's Whisper forces Defense Checks before enemies can act, and her Charm can turn entire groups against each other. She works only for payment in magic items that might restore her true form. Extremely dangerous in social situations.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 56, 57","key":"source.the-silent-the-mermaid-assassin","owner":"The Silent (The Mermaid Assassin)","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"009tdx5nn5xdt900","name":"The Wild Swans Gang","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-wild-swans-gang","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[55,56]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"La Banda de los Cisnes Salvajes","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 55, 56. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Intermedio 5","impulse":"Defeat the Hunters of the Order and find Elisa / Save Elisa from the clutches of the Order, even if it means destroying it","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 55, 56."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defeat the Hunters of the Order and find Elisa / Save Elisa from the clutches of the Order, even if it means destroying it","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"009j9uvggvu9j900","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-wild-swans-gang","ownerKey":"the-wild-swans-gang","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a band of brothers and we specialize in fighting the Order's emissaries</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 55, 56","key":"descriptor-principal.the-wild-swans-gang","owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"We are a band of brothers and we specialize in fighting the Order's emissaries","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"00ad8nyddyn8da00","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor1-don1.the-wild-swans-gang","ownerKey":"the-wild-swans-gang","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor 2"}},"role":"gift-descriptor","descriptorRole":"gift-descriptor"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the curse that has been inflicted on us, we can transform into swans</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 55, 56","key":"descriptor1-don1.the-wild-swans-gang","owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"Thanks to the curse that has been inflicted on us, we can transform into swans","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01bjntuzzutnjb10","name":"Gift - Changed into a Swan","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-wild-swans-gang","ownerKey":"the-wild-swans-gang","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Convertirse en cisne"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A member of the Wild Swans Gang can transform into a swan at will. The transformation is immediate. When it happens, it gives him the new Descriptor: I am a wild swan – I can fly well, but I maintain my human consciousness. The gang member's clothing, items, and other possessions are never lost during the transformation.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 55, 56","key":"don1.the-wild-swans-gang","owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01btnfjyyjfntb10","name":"Gift - The Swans Gang","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-wild-swans-gang","ownerKey":"the-wild-swans-gang","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Bandada de cisnes"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>When a member of the gang acts and has at least one partner to support him, he increases his Opposition Level by 1. If at least 3 members focus on supporting the same action, whoever performs it increases the Opposition Level by 3 points.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 55, 56","key":"don2.the-wild-swans-gang","owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"013xan5qq5nax310","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-wild-swans-gang","ownerKey":"the-wild-swans-gang","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 55]<br>50<br>La Banda de los<br>Cisnes Salvajes<br>Inspirado en Los cisnes salvajes (oponente)<br>Érase una vez once hermanos audaces, hijos de un noble afable. Todos estaban<br>profundamente unidos a su hermana menor, Elisa, y la trataban como a una<br>reina. Cuando el padre volvió a casarse, la nueva esposa, celosa de toda la<br>atención que la familia reservaba a Elisa, hizo un pacto con Morgana, la famo­<br>sa bruja, para lanzar una poderosa maldición. Los hermanos se convirtieron<br>en cisnes y Elisa fue culpada por ello. Acusada de hechicera y expulsada por<br>su padre, vagó durante meses en busca de un nuevo hogar. Finalmente llegó<br>a otra región, donde fue acogida por un noble local que pronto se enamoró<br>de su belleza. Elisa comenzó a vivir con alegría, reuniéndose regularmente<br>con sus hermanos, que mientras tanto habían estado buscando una forma de<br>romper la maldición que les habían lanzado. Elisa comenzó a estudiar magia<br>para ayudarles, pero esto atrajo la atención del prelado del país que, temiendo<br>lo peor, solicitó la intervención de la Orden. Al llegar ante Elisa, los Cazadores<br>advirtieron su predisposición por la magia y se la llevaron, entregándola a los<br>inquisidores papales. Cuando los once hermanos se enteraron, lloraron amarga­<br>mente por el destino de su hermana y juraron vengarse de la Orden, lo que hizo<br>que emprendieran una guerra con la esperanza de encontrar a Elisa con vida.<br>Descriptor:  somos una banda de hermanos y estamos especializados en<br>combatir a los emisarios de la Orden. Gracias a la maldición que nos ha sido<br>impuesta, podemos transformarnos en cisnes.<br>1 Herida (para cada uno de los 11 miembros de la banda)<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5</p><p>[Manual Básico, p. 56]<br>51<br>Objetivo: derrotar a los Cazadores de la Orden y encontrar<br>a Elisa. Salvar a Elisa de las garras de la Orden, aunque sig­<br>nifique su destrucción.<br>Objetivo especial (Morgana del Lago):  hemos descu­<br>bierto que todo lo que nos ha pasado es culpa de la bruja<br>Morgana, así que queremos secuestrarla y obligarla a salvar<br>a Elisa con su magia.<br>Nota: Morgana del Lago es una de las Cazadoras que apa-<br>recen en el suplemento The Broken Ones.<br>Don: Convertirse en cisne. Un miembro de la Banda de<br>los Cisnes Salvajes puede transformarse en cisne a volun-<br>tad. La transformación es inmediata. Cuando ocurre, le da<br>el nuevo descriptor: soy un cisne salvaje, puedo volar, pero<br>mantengo mi conciencia humana. La ropa, los objetos y otras<br>pertenencias del miembro de la banda no se pierden durante<br>la transformación.<br>Don: Bandada de cisnes.  Cuando un miembro de la<br>banda actúa y tiene al menos un compañero que le apoya,<br>aumenta su Nivel de Oposición en 1. Si al menos tres miem-<br>bros se concentran en apoyar la misma acción, quien la lleva<br>a cabo aumenta su Nivel de Oposición en 3 puntos.<br>La Silenciosa<br>Inspirada en La sirenita (oponente)<br>Érase una vez una joven sirena que fue capturada por un<br>pescador. Al percibir su valor, el codicioso pescador la entregó<br>como tributo al noble local, que la exhibió como un animal<br>exótico, fascinando a todo el mundo, pero especialmente a su<br>hijo. Con el tiempo, el joven aristócrata empezó a mirar a la<br>sirena con otros ojos, y su curiosidad se convirtió en pasión.<br>Ambos consumaron un deseo prohibido, que llevó a la joven<br>sirena a sentir un amor sincero por su príncipe. El sentimien­<br>to, por desgracia, no fue correspondido. En cuanto se presentó<br>la oportunidad, el hijo del noble abandonó la casa familiar<br>para casarse. La sirena fue vendida a un circo, destinada a<br>terminar sus días como monstruo de feria, asustando a los<br>necios con su miseria. El encuentro con una misteriosa bruja<br>llamada Marina cambió su destino. A cambio de su voz, ob­<br>tuvo una poción para cambiar de forma.<br>—Ten cuidado —dijo la bruja—. ¿De verdad quieres renun­<br>ciar a lo que eres para perseguir un amor fugaz?<br>La sirena no se lo pensó dos veces y se bebió la poción para<br>ser completamente humana. Volvió con su príncipe, solo para<br>descubrir que él apenas se acordaba de ella y del tiempo que<br>habían pasado juntos. El corazón de la sirena se ensombreció.<br>En una noche de luna llena, bebió la sangre de su amor per­<br>dido, además de la de toda su nueva familia.<br>Descriptor: soy una asesina sin escrúpulos, odio a la huma­<br>nidad y el cuerpo al que estoy condenada. Mi voz se reduce a<br>un débil susurro, lo que ha debilitado mis poderes de sirena,<br>pero no me los ha quitado.<br>3 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Intermedio 5</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once upon a time, there were eleven bold brothers, sons of an amiable nobleman. All were deeply attached to their younger sister Elisa and treated her like a queen. When the father remarried, the new wife, jealous of all the attention that the family reserved for Elisa, made a pact with Morgana, the famous witch, to cast a powerful curse. The brothers were turned into swans and Elisa was blamed for it. Accused of being a sorcerer and cast out by her father, Elisa wandered for months looking for a new home. Finally, she reached another region, where she was welcomed by a local noble who soon fell in love with her beauty. Elisa began living happily, regularly meeting her brothers, who in the meantime had been looking for a way to break the curse cast upon them. Elisa started to study magic to help them, but this attracted the attention of the prelate of the country who, fearing the worst, requested the Order's intervention. Upon reaching Elisa's presence, the Hunters noted her propensity for magic and took her away, turning her over to the papal inquisitors. When the eleven brothers found out, they cried bitter tears for their sister's fate and swore revenge against the Order, waging war in the hope of finding Elisa alive.</p><p>SPECIAL AGENDA (Morgana of the Lake): We learned that everything that happened to us is the fault of Morgana the Witch, so we want to kidnap and force her to save Elisa with her magic.</p><p>IMPORTANT: There are 11 gang members total, each with 1 Wound and OL Medium 5. They become significantly more powerful when working together - 3+ members supporting an action increases OL by 3! They can transform into swans for mobility and reconnaissance. They are driven by love for their sister and hatred of the Order.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 55, 56","key":"source.the-wild-swans-gang","owner":"The Wild Swans Gang","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"01lstxlqqlxtsl10","name":"The Wise Fox","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"00n6bknu004e8l47","flags":{"broken-tales":{"darkPresenceSlug":"the-wise-fox","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Dark Presences.db","sourceBackup":"E:/respaldos/Dark Presences.db","sourcePages":{"es":[58]},"translations":{"es":{"name":"El Zorro Sabio","system":{"details":{"concept":"Presencia oscura","origin":"Manual Básico","role":"Presencia oscura","notes":"Manual Básico, páginas 58. Restaurado desde respaldo."},"threat":{"rank":"Difícil 7","impulse":"To help the humans I deem deserving while asking a fair price in exchange","oppositionLevel":7}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Dark Presence","origin":"Core Book","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"Core Book. Restored from backup Dark Presences.db. Spanish source pages: 58."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"To help the humans I deem deserving while asking a fair price in exchange","oppositionLevel":7}},"items":[{"_id":"0004z9n11n9z4000","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"descriptor-principal.the-wise-fox","ownerKey":"the-wise-fox","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Descriptor principal"}},"role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an immortal spirit incarnated in the body of a talking fox and I have always watched over human affairs</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 58","key":"descriptor-principal.the-wise-fox","owner":"The Wise Fox","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","positive":"I am an immortal spirit incarnated in the body of a talking fox and I have always watched over human affairs","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01hqqqeyyeqqqh10","name":"Gift - A Good Advice","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don1.the-wise-fox","ownerKey":"the-wise-fox","sequence":1,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Un buen consejo"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, the Wise Fox can appear to someone who has done a good deed, to bring advice, an object, or information that will be decisive for the current Scene. Before dispensing his help, however, the Fox will ask for a price to be paid. Select between: 1. Spilled Blood: Whoever benefits from the advice must self-inflict 1 Wound by shedding blood as a symbol of commitment. 2. Good Action: Whoever wants to receive the Fox's help will first have to perform the requested action. This action, although apparently absurd, can be contextualized by the Storyteller in a future Scenario faced by the Hunters. The effort required must include difficult or dangerous situations to overcome. 3. Demonstrate Commitment: To receive the benefit of the advice, a Hunter has to go through an entire Scene without using Gifts.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 58","key":"don1.the-wise-fox","owner":"The Wise Fox","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01hgr4pzzp4rgh10","name":"Gift - Offer Help","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"don2.the-wise-fox","ownerKey":"the-wise-fox","sequence":2,"collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Don: Ofrecer ayuda"}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, the Wise Fox can appear and help one who previously paid the cost he required. A Hunter may spend 1 Soma to get advice from the Wise Fox, thus receiving 2 Additional Successes on a Position Check.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 58","key":"don2.the-wise-fox","owner":"The Wise Fox","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"01rklo4vv4olkr10","name":"Source","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"contentKey":"source.the-wise-fox","ownerKey":"the-wise-fox","collection":"Core Book","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fuente española","system":{"description":"<p>[Manual Básico, p. 58]<br>53<br>El Zorro Sabio<br>Inspirado en El pájaro de oro (aliado)<br>Desde tiempos inmemoriales, hay quienes han dejado de lado<br>las sabias palabras que aconsejaban el trabajo duro y la res­<br>ponsabilidad, prefiriendo las recompensas rápidas y fáciles.<br>Cuando se ignoran las lecciones de los sabios, el dolor<br>es el maestro por excelencia, trayendo consigo la con­<br>ciencia de que todo error tiene un precio. Un espíritu<br>benévolo y bondadoso lo sabía bien y durante siglos<br>había intentado enseñar a los mortales para evitarles<br>el dolor de una lección más dura, solo para verlos<br>elegir inevitablemente el camino menos sensato.<br>Finalmente, el espíritu decidió ayudar a los nece­<br>sitados, pero solo si podían pagar su precio. De<br>este modo, pensó, su ayuda sería más apre­<br>ciada por los humanos, que consideran<br>algo más valioso cuanto más les cuesta.<br>Descriptor: soy un espíritu inmortal<br>encarnado en el cuerpo de un zorro que<br>habla y siempre he estado pendiente de<br>los asuntos humanos.<br>6 Heridas<br>Nivel de Oposición: Difícil 7<br>Objetivo: ayudar a los humanos que con­<br>sidero que lo merecen pidiendo a cambio<br>un precio justo.<br>Don: Un buen consejo. Una vez por<br>escena, el Zorro Sabio puede aparecerse<br>a alguien que haya realizado una buena<br>acción para darle un consejo, un objeto o una información<br>que será decisiva para la escena en curso. Sin embargo, an-<br>tes de dispensar su ayuda, el Zorro pedirá que se pague un<br>precio. Elige entre: 1. Sangre derramada: quien se be-<br>neficie de los consejos debe infligirse 1 Herida derramando<br>sangre como símbolo de compromiso. 2. Buena acción:<br>quien quiera recibir la ayuda del Zorro tendrá que reali-<br>zar primero la acción solicitada. Esta acción, aunque<br>aparentemente absurda, puede ser contextualizada<br>por el Narrador en un futuro escenario al que se<br>enfrenten los Cazadores. El esfuerzo requerido<br>debe incluir situaciones difíciles o peligrosas. 3.<br>Muestra de compromiso: para obtener el<br>beneficio del consejo, un Cazador tiene que<br>pasar toda una escena sin usar dones.<br>Don: Ofrecer ayuda. Una vez por escena,<br>el Zorro Sabio puede aparecer y ayudar a<br>alguien que haya pagado previamen-<br>te el coste que requirió. Un Cazador<br>puede gastar 1 Soma para obtener<br>consejo del Zorro Sabio, con lo que<br>obtiene 2 Éxitos adicionales en una<br>prueba de posición.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Since time immemorial some have set aside the wise words that advised hard work and responsibility, preferring fast and easy rewards. When the lessons of the wise are ignored, pain is the teacher of last resort, bringing with it the awareness that every mistake has a price. A benevolent and kind Spirit knew this well and for centuries had tried to teach mortals in order to spare them the pain of a harsher lesson, only to see them inevitably choose the less sensible path. Eventually, the Spirit decided to help those in need, but only if they could meet his price. In this way, he thought, his help would be more appreciated by humans, who value something more the more it costs them.</p><p>The Wise Fox is a powerful ally who helps those who prove themselves worthy by paying a price. His advice can be game-changing, providing critical information or +2 Successes. However, he always demands payment first: spilled blood (1 Wound), a dangerous task, or commitment (no Gifts for a Scene). He appears to those who do good deeds. With 6 Wounds and OL 7, he's nearly unkillable if attacked.</p>","notes":"Backup: Dark Presences.db / Manual Básico p. 58","key":"source.the-wise-fox","owner":"The Wise Fox","category":"darkPresence","source":"Core Book"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.15","createdTime":1784372541845,"modifiedTime":1784372541845,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
